dot1dTpPortOutFrames.description: The number of frames that have been transmitted by this port to its segment. Note that a frame transmitted on the interface corresponding to this port is only counted by this object if and only if it is for a protocol being processed by the local bridging function, including bridge management frames.

dot1dTpPortInDiscards.name: dot1dTpPortInDiscards
dot1dTpPortInDiscards.description: Count of valid frames received which were discarded (i.e., filtered) by the Forwarding Process.

dot1dStaticTable.name: dot1dStaticTable
dot1dStaticTable.description: A table containing filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from specific ports and containing specific destination addresses are allowed to be forwarded. The value of zero in this table as the port number from which frames with a specific destination address are received, is used to specify all ports for which there is no specific entry in this table for that particular destination address. Entries are valid for unicast and for group/broadcast addresses.

dot1dStaticEntry.name: dot1dStaticEntry
dot1dStaticEntry.description: Filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and containing a specific destination address are allowed to be forwarded.

dot1dStaticAddress.name: dot1dStaticAddress
dot1dStaticAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies. This object can take the value of a unicast address, a group address or the broadcast address.

dot1dStaticReceivePort.name: dot1dStaticReceivePort
dot1dStaticReceivePort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port from which a frame must be received in order for this entry's filtering information to apply. A value of zero indicates that this entry applies on all ports of the bridge for which there is no other applicable entry.

dot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.name: dot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo
dot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.description: The set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and destined for a specific MAC address, are allowed to be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.) The default value of this object is a string of ones of appropriate length.

dot1dStaticStatus.name: dot1dStaticStatus
dot1dStaticStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. The default value is permanent(3). other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry. permanent(3) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnReset(4) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnTimeout(5) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until it is aged out.

newRoot.name: newRoot
newRoot.description: The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election. Implementation of this trap is optional.

topologyChange.name: topologyChange
topologyChange.description: A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition. Implementation of this trap is optional.

pppLinkStatusTable.name: pppLinkStatusTable
pppLinkStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP-link specific variables for this PPP implementation.

pppLinkStatusEntry.name: pppLinkStatusEntry
pppLinkStatusEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP Link.

pppLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.name: pppLinkStatusPhysicalIndex
pppLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.description: The value of ifIndex that identifies the lower-level interface over which this PPP Link is operating. This interface would usually be an HDLC or RS-232 type of interface. If there is no lower-layer interface element, or there is no ifEntry for the element, or the element can not be identified, then the value of this object is 0. For example, suppose that PPP is operating over a serial port. This would use two entries in the ifTable. The PPP could be running over `interface' number 123 and the serial port could be running over `interface' number 987. Therefore, ifSpecific.123 would contain the OBJECT IDENTIFIER ppp pppLinkStatusPhysicalIndex.123 would contain 987, and ifSpecific.987 would contain the OBJECT IDENTIFIER for the serial-port's media- specific MIB.

pppLinkStatusBadAddresses.name: pppLinkStatusBadAddresses
pppLinkStatusBadAddresses.description: The number of packets received with an incorrect Address Field. This counter is a component of the ifInErrors variable that is associated with the interface that represents this PPP Link.

pppLinkStatusBadControls.name: pppLinkStatusBadControls
pppLinkStatusBadControls.description: The number of packets received on this link with an incorrect Control Field. This counter is a component of the ifInErrors variable that is associated with the interface that represents this PPP Link.

pppLinkStatusPacketTooLongs.name: pppLinkStatusPacketTooLongs
pppLinkStatusPacketTooLongs.description: The number of received packets that have been discarded because their length exceeded the MRU. This counter is a component of the ifInErrors variable that is associated with the interface that represents this PPP Link. NOTE, packets which are longer than the MRU but which are successfully received and processed are NOT included in this count.

pppLinkStatusBadFCSs.name: pppLinkStatusBadFCSs
pppLinkStatusBadFCSs.description: The number of received packets that have been discarded due to having an incorrect FCS. This counter is a component of the ifInErrors variable that is associated with the interface that represents this PPP Link.

pppLinkStatusLocalMRU.name: pppLinkStatusLocalMRU
pppLinkStatusLocalMRU.description: The current value of the MRU for the local PPP Entity. This value is the MRU that the remote entity is using when sending packets to the local PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusRemoteMRU.name: pppLinkStatusRemoteMRU
pppLinkStatusRemoteMRU.description: The current value of the MRU for the remote PPP Entity. This value is the MRU that the local entity is using when sending packets to the remote PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusLocalToPeerACCMap.name: pppLinkStatusLocalToPeerACCMap
pppLinkStatusLocalToPeerACCMap.description: The current value of the ACC Map used for sending packets from the local PPP entity to the remote PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusPeerToLocalACCMap.name: pppLinkStatusPeerToLocalACCMap
pppLinkStatusPeerToLocalACCMap.description: The ACC Map used by the remote PPP entity when transmitting packets to the local PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteProtocolCompre.name: pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteProtocolCompression
pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteProtocolCompre.description: Indicates whether the local PPP entity will use Protocol Compression when transmitting packets to the remote PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalProtocolCompre.name: pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalProtocolCompression
pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalProtocolCompre.description: Indicates whether the remote PPP entity will use Protocol Compression when transmitting packets to the local PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteACCompression.name: pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteACCompression
pppLinkStatusLocalToRemoteACCompression.description: Indicates whether the local PPP entity will use Address and Control Compression when transmitting packets to the remote PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalACCompression.name: pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalACCompression
pppLinkStatusRemoteToLocalACCompression.description: Indicates whether the remote PPP entity will use Address and Control Compression when transmitting packets to the local PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusTransmitFcsSize.name: pppLinkStatusTransmitFcsSize
pppLinkStatusTransmitFcsSize.description: The size of the Frame Check Sequence (FCS) in bits that the local node will generate when sending packets to the remote node. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkStatusReceiveFcsSize.name: pppLinkStatusReceiveFcsSize
pppLinkStatusReceiveFcsSize.description: The size of the Frame Check Sequence (FCS) in bits that the remote node will generate when sending packets to the local node. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

pppLinkConfigTable.name: pppLinkConfigTable
pppLinkConfigTable.description: A table containing the LCP configuration parameters for this PPP Link. These variables represent the initial configuration of the PPP Link. The actual values of the parameters may be changed when the link is brought up via the LCP options negotiation mechanism.

pppLinkConfigEntry.name: pppLinkConfigEntry
pppLinkConfigEntry.description: Configuration information about a particular PPP Link.

pppLinkConfigInitialMRU.name: pppLinkConfigInitialMRU
pppLinkConfigInitialMRU.reference: Section 7.2, Maximum Receive Unit of RFC1331.
pppLinkConfigInitialMRU.description: The initial Maximum Receive Unit (MRU) that the local PPP entity will advertise to the remote entity. If the value of this variable is 0 then the local PPP entity will not advertise any MRU to the remote entity and the default MRU will be assumed. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted. Agent variations: DESCRIPTION writing not supported

pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap.name: pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap
pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap.reference: Section 7.3, page 4, Async-Control-Character- Map of RFC1331.
pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap.description: The Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map (ACC) that the local PPP entity requires for use on its receive side. In effect, this is the ACC Map that is required in order to ensure that the local modem will successfully receive all characters. The actual ACC map used on the receive side of the link will be a combination of the local node's pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap and the remote node's pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted.

pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap.name: pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap
pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap.reference: Section 7.3, page 4, Async-Control-Character- Map of RFC1331.
pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap.description: The Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map (ACC) that the local PPP entity requires for use on its transmit side. In effect, this is the ACC Map that is required in order to ensure that all characters can be successfully transmitted through the local modem. The actual ACC map used on the transmit side of the link will be a combination of the local node's pppLinkConfigTransmitACCMap and the remote node's pppLinkConfigReceiveACCMap. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted. Agent variations: DESCRIPTION writing not supported

pppLinkConfigMagicNumber.name: pppLinkConfigMagicNumber
pppLinkConfigMagicNumber.description: If true(2) then the local node will attempt to perform Magic Number negotiation with the remote node. If false(1) then this negotiation is not performed. In any event, the local node will comply with any magic number negotiations attempted by the remote node, per the PPP specification. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted. Agent variations: DESCRIPTION writing not supported

pppLinkConfigFcsSize.name: pppLinkConfigFcsSize
pppLinkConfigFcsSize.description: The size of the FCS, in bits, the local node will attempt to negotiate for use with the remote node. Regardless of the value of this object, the local node will comply with any FCS size negotiations initiated by the remote node, per the PPP specification. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted. Agent variations: DESCRIPTION writing not supported

pppIpTable.name: pppIpTable
pppIpTable.description: Table containing the IP parameters and statistics for the local PPP entity.

pppIpEntry.name: pppIpEntry
pppIpEntry.description: IPCP status information for a particular PPP link.

pppIpOperStatus.name: pppIpOperStatus
pppIpOperStatus.description: The operational status of the IP network protocol. If the value of this object is up then the finite state machine for the IP network protocol has reached the Opened state.

pppIpLocalToRemoteCompressionProtocol.name: pppIpLocalToRemoteCompressionProtocol
pppIpLocalToRemoteCompressionProtocol.description: The IP compression protocol that the local PPP-IP entity uses when sending packets to the remote PPP-IP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (pppIpOperStatus is opened).

pppIpRemoteToLocalCompressionProtocol.name: pppIpRemoteToLocalCompressionProtocol
pppIpRemoteToLocalCompressionProtocol.description: The IP compression protocol that the remote PPP-IP entity uses when sending packets to the local PPP-IP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (pppIpOperStatus is opened).

pppIpRemoteMaxSlotId.name: pppIpRemoteMaxSlotId
pppIpRemoteMaxSlotId.description: The Max-Slot-Id parameter that the remote node has advertised and that is in use on the link. If vj-tcp header compression is not in use on the link then the value of this object shall be 0. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (pppIpOperStatus is opened).

pppIpLocalMaxSlotId.name: pppIpLocalMaxSlotId
pppIpLocalMaxSlotId.description: The Max-Slot-Id parameter that the local node has advertised and that is in use on the link. If vj-tcp header compression is not in use on the link then the value of this object shall be 0. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (pppIpOperStatus is opened).

pppIpConfigTable.name: pppIpConfigTable
pppIpConfigTable.description: Table containing configuration variables for the IPCP for the local PPP entity.

pppIpConfigEntry.name: pppIpConfigEntry
pppIpConfigEntry.description: IPCP information for a particular PPP link.

pppIpConfigAdminStatus.name: pppIpConfigAdminStatus
pppIpConfigAdminStatus.description: The immediate desired status of the IP network protocol. Setting this object to open will inject an administrative open event into the IP network protocol's finite state machine. Setting this object to close will inject an administrative close event into the IP network protocol's finite state machine. Agent variations: DESCRIPTION writing not supported

pppIpConfigCompression.name: pppIpConfigCompression
pppIpConfigCompression.reference: Section 4.0, Van Jacobson TCP/IP Header Compression of RFC1332.
pppIpConfigCompression.description: If none(1) then the local node will not attempt to negotiate any IP Compression option. Otherwise, the local node will attempt to negotiate compression mode indicated by the enumerated value. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted.

appleState.name: appleState
appleState.description: Controls whether the router will perform AppleTalk routing.

appleStatus.name: appleStatus
appleStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is performing AppleTalk routing.

appleStatusIf.name: appleStatusIf
appleStatusIf.description: The ifIndex of the bad interface if appleStatus is 'badConfig'.

applePortTable.name: applePortTable
applePortTable.description: Table of fields indexed by interface.

applePortIndex.name: applePortIndex
applePortIndex.description: The index of the interface; same as IfIndex.

applePortProtocolPriority.name: applePortProtocolPriority
applePortProtocolPriority.description: This value defines the priority at which all Apple routed packets will be placed on the WAN output queue.

applePortArpInterval.name: applePortArpInterval
applePortArpInterval.description: The interval at which ARP messages should be sent during the process of selecting a network address.

applePortArpRetransmitCount.name: applePortArpRetransmitCount
applePortArpRetransmitCount.description: The number of ARP messages that should be sent during the process of selecting a network address.

applePortChecksum.name: applePortChecksum
applePortChecksum.description: Controls whether checksums are generated on all DDP packets sent out the interface.

applePortPacketsIn.name: applePortPacketsIn
applePortPacketsIn.description: The number of AppleTalk packets received on this interface.

applePortPacketsOut.name: applePortPacketsOut
applePortPacketsOut.description: The number of AppleTalk packets transmitted on this interface.

applePortForwardsIn.name: applePortForwardsIn
applePortForwardsIn.description: The number of AppleTalk packets received on this interface which were not addressed to this router.

applePortForwardsOut.name: applePortForwardsOut
applePortForwardsOut.description: The number of AppleTalk packets transmitted on this interface which were not originated by this router.

applePortNetAddress.name: applePortNetAddress
applePortNetAddress.description: The actual address used by this port.

applePortNetStart.name: applePortNetStart
applePortNetStart.description: The start of the actual network range used by this port.

applePortNetEnd.name: applePortNetEnd
applePortNetEnd.description: The end of the actual network range used by this port.

applePortErrors.name: applePortErrors
applePortErrors.description: The number of AppleTalk packets received in error.

applePortLastError.name: applePortLastError
applePortLastError.description: The type of the most recent error counted in applePortErrors. A value of zero means no error.

applePortLastErrorTime.name: applePortLastErrorTime
applePortLastErrorTime.description: The value of sysUptime when applePortLastError last occured.

applePortLastErrorData.name: applePortLastErrorData
applePortLastErrorData.description: The first 22 bytes of the packet from applePortLastError.

applePortBringBackTime.name: applePortBringBackTime
applePortBringBackTime.description: The number of seconds to shut down an interface while waiting for a manager-initiated configuration change to propagate.

applePortUseNeighborNotify.name: applePortUseNeighborNotify
applePortUseNeighborNotify.description: Controls generation of neighbor notify messages when an interface is disabled or system is shut down.

applePortRouterType.name: applePortRouterType
applePortRouterType.description: Type of router operation over this port.

applePortZoneTable.name: applePortZoneTable
applePortZoneTable.description: Table of fields indexed by interface and zone.

applePortZoneIndex.name: applePortZoneIndex
applePortZoneIndex.description: The index of the interface; same as IfIndex.

applePortZoneStatus.name: applePortZoneStatus
applePortZoneStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

applePortExportTable.name: applePortExportTable
applePortExportTable.description: Table of fields indexed by interface and zone.

applePortExportIndex.name: applePortExportIndex
applePortExportIndex.description: The index of the interface; same as IfIndex.

applePortExportAction.name: applePortExportAction
applePortExportAction.description: Control whether the data will be hidden or advertised.

applePortExportStatus.name: applePortExportStatus
applePortExportStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

applePortImportTable.name: applePortImportTable
applePortImportTable.description: Table of fields indexed by interface and zone.

applePortImportIndex.name: applePortImportIndex
applePortImportIndex.description: The index of the interface; same as IfIndex.

applePortImportAction.name: applePortImportAction
applePortImportAction.description: Control whether the data will be discarded or accepted.

applePortImportStatus.name: applePortImportStatus
applePortImportStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

appleNbpTable.name: appleNbpTable
appleNbpTable.description: Table of fields indexed by interface and zone.

appleNbpNode.name: appleNbpNode
appleNbpNode.description: The address of the node who offers the service associated with this entry.

appleNbpSocket.name: appleNbpSocket
appleNbpSocket.description: The socket of the service associated with this entry. The value 0 means no socket.

appleTrafficSort.name: appleTrafficSort
appleTrafficSort.description: Setting to EXECUTE causes the most recent traffic information to be sorted into the appleTrafficTable. The sorting precedence is: decreasing percentage, increasing destination address, increasing source address, and increasing interface number. Setting to READY has no effect.

appleTrafficTable.name: appleTrafficTable
appleTrafficTable.description: A list of traffic entries, sorted in the order specified by appleTrafficSort.

appleTrafficEntry.name: appleTrafficEntry
appleTrafficEntry.description: Parameter values for an Filter filter.

appleTrafficPercent.name: appleTrafficPercent
appleTrafficPercent.description: The percent of total traffic that this traffic entryrepresents, in tenths of a percent.

appleTrafficDst.name: appleTrafficDst
appleTrafficDst.description: The destination to which the traffic entry applies.

appleTrafficSrc.name: appleTrafficSrc
appleTrafficSrc.description: The source to which the traffic entry applies.

appleTrafficIntf.name: appleTrafficIntf
appleTrafficIntf.description: The inbound interface to which the traffic entry applies.

appleTrafficMonitoring.name: appleTrafficMonitoring
appleTrafficMonitoring.description: Controls whether internet traffic information will be recorded.

arapPassword.name: arapPassword
arapPassword.description: The server's ARAP password. To increase security, Gets of this object return the NULL string.

arapDefaultZoneName.name: arapDefaultZoneName
arapDefaultZoneName.description: The name of the AppleTalk zone that the server should try to choose at boot time.

arapPortTable.name: arapPortTable
arapPortTable.description: A list of ARAP port entries.

arapPortEntry.name: arapPortEntry
arapPortEntry.description: ARAP parameter values for a port.

arapPortEnabled.name: arapPortEnabled
arapPortEnabled.description: Indicates if ARAP connections are allowed on this port.

arapPortZoneAccess.name: arapPortZoneAccess
arapPortZoneAccess.description: Indicates the AppleTalk zones that ARAP connections on this port may access: none, local, all, or named zone.

arapPortZoneName.name: arapPortZoneName
arapPortZoneName.description: If this port's arapPortZoneAccess field indicates a named zone, this field contains the zone name.

arapPortMaxConnectTime.name: arapPortMaxConnectTime
arapPortMaxConnectTime.description: Maximum number of minutes a single ARAP connection may exist on the port before a server initiated disconnect. To set no limit on the amount of time that an ARAP user may be connected, set this object to -1.

arapPortGuestLoginsOk.name: arapPortGuestLoginsOk
arapPortGuestLoginsOk.description: Indicates if 'Guest' logins (with no password) are allowed on the port.

arapPortTimeConnected.name: arapPortTimeConnected
arapPortTimeConnected.description: Indicates the number of minutes the current ARAP connection has been established on the port, rounded up to the nearest minute. Gets return -1 if no ARAP user is currently connected on the port or if ARAP is not enabled on the port.

arapPortTimeRemaining.name: arapPortTimeRemaining
arapPortTimeRemaining.description: Indicates the number of minutes the current ARAP connection may remain on the port before a server initiated disconnect will occur, rounded up to the nearest minute. To set no limit on the amount of time that the current ARAP user may continue to be connected, set this object to the maximum value in the range. Gets return -1 if no ARAP user is currently connected on the port or if ARAP is not enabled on the port. Gets also return -1 if there is a user connected and there is no limit on the amount of time that the current user may be connected.

bootClientStatus.name: bootClientStatus
bootClientStatus.description: The overall status of the bootstrapping operation, including, for example, what is presently happening and error information.

basicLogLimit.name: basicLogLimit
basicLogLimit.description: Maximum allowed number of kilobytes for recording events. Corresponds directly to MANAGER LOG FILE SIZE and the value labeled 'Log File Size:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicActiveLimit.name: basicActiveLimit
basicActiveLimit.description: Maximum allowed number of simultaneous service dialogs. Corresponds directly to MANAGER SIMULTANEOUS and the value labeled 'Maximum simultaneous requests:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicActiveNumber.name: basicActiveNumber
basicActiveNumber.description: Number of active service dialogs. Corresponds indirectly to the list of active clients in the MANAGER STATUS display.

basicClientNumber.name: basicClientNumber
basicClientNumber.description: Number of defined clients. Corresponds indirectly to the list of defined clients in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

basicOffersSent.name: basicOffersSent
basicOffersSent.description: Total number of service offers sent in response to client requests. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Total service offers sent:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

basicEventTotal.name: basicEventTotal
basicEventTotal.description: Total number of events that have been written to the event log since it was last purged. This may be less than the number currently in the log. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Total Messages Logged:' in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

basicEventPurge.name: basicEventPurge
basicEventPurge.description: Control to cause emptying the event log. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the event log to immediately become empty. Corresponds directly to the PURGE MANAGER LOG FILE command.

activeTable.name: activeTable
activeTable.description: A list of active client dialog entries. The number of entries is given by basicActiveNumber.

activeEntry.name: activeEntry
activeEntry.description: Parameter values for an active client dialog entry.

activeIdentificationType.name: activeIdentificationType
activeIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in activeIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to the value labeled 'EthernetAddress' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeIdentification.name: activeIdentification
activeIdentification.description: Identification of the active partner. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'EthernetAddress' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeFunction.name: activeFunction
activeFunction.description: The function the server is performing with the partner. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Function' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeSoftwareVersionType.name: activeSoftwareVersionType
activeSoftwareVersionType.description: If activeFunction is 'load', the software version being sent to the client, otherwise 'notApplicable'. Corresponds to the letter in the software version labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display. alpha 'A': alpha test beta 'B': beta test production null: normal, production software special 'S': special, custom software diagnostic 'D': diagnostic, debug software

activeSoftwareVersion.name: activeSoftwareVersion
activeSoftwareVersion.description: If activeFunction is 'load', the 4-byte software version being sent to the client, otherwise zero length. In order, the octets contain major version, minor version, ECO, and pre-release number. Corresponds to the numbers in the software version labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display. For example, the version display for activeSoftwareVersionType 'production' and activeSoftwareVersion '2.2.0.0' is 'V2.2'. The version display for activeSoftwareVersionType 'beta' and activeSoftwareVersion '3.1.0.4' is 'V3.1B4'.

activeParameterVersion.name: activeParameterVersion
activeParameterVersion.description: If activeFunction is 'parameterStore', the parameter version being stored by the client, otherwise zero. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeCurrentSequence.name: activeCurrentSequence
activeCurrentSequence.description: The current dialog sequence number. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Seq' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeBytesRemaining.name: activeBytesRemaining
activeBytesRemaining.description: The number of bytes remaining to be transferred in the dialog. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Left' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeFile.name: activeFile
activeFile.description: The name of the file being used in the dialog. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'File' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeStatus.name: activeStatus
activeStatus.description: The final status of the most recent attempt to get an image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Get Status:' in the DEVICE STATUS display.

activeState.name: activeState
activeState.description: The dynamic state of an active attempt to get an image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Get State:' in the DEVICE STATUS display.

clientTable.name: clientTable
clientTable.description: A list of client data base entries. The number of entries is given by basicClientNumber.

clientEntry.name: clientEntry
clientEntry.description: Parameter values for a client data base entry.

clientIdentificationType.name: clientIdentificationType
clientIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in clientIdentification. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

clientIdentification.name: clientIdentification
clientIdentification.description: Identification of the client, either a hardware type or an Ethernet address, depending on clientIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

clientEntryStatus.name: clientEntryStatus
clientEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the PURGE LOCAL, PURGE GLOBAL, and PURGE NODE commands. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

clientName.name: clientName
clientName.description: A name that may be used to identify the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Name' in the MANAGER NODE display.

clientLoadFile.name: clientLoadFile
clientLoadFile.description: The file with the client's load image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientDiagnosticFile.name: clientDiagnosticFile
clientDiagnosticFile.description: The file with the client's diagnostic test image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Diag File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientLoadService.name: clientLoadService
clientLoadService.description: Control for allowing load service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientDumpService.name: clientDumpService
clientDumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedTable.name: namedTable
namedTable.description: A list of named client data base entries. The number of entries is given by basicClientNumber.

namedEntry.name: namedEntry
namedEntry.description: Parameter values for a named client data base entry.

namedIdentificationType.name: namedIdentificationType
namedIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in namedIdentification. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

namedIdentification.name: namedIdentification
namedIdentification.description: Identification of the client, either a hardware type or an Ethernet address, depending on namedIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

namedEntryStatus.name: namedEntryStatus
namedEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the PURGE LOCAL, PURGE GLOBAL, and PURGE NODE commands. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

namedName.name: namedName
namedName.description: A name that may be used to identify the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Name' in the MANAGER NODE display.

namedLoadFile.name: namedLoadFile
namedLoadFile.description: The file with the client's load image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedDiagnosticFile.name: namedDiagnosticFile
namedDiagnosticFile.description: The file with the client's diagnostic test image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Diag File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedLoadService.name: namedLoadService
namedLoadService.description: Control for allowing load service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedDumpService.name: namedDumpService
namedDumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

xEventTable.name: xEventTable
xEventTable.description: A list of event entries. The number of entries is given by basicEventNumber.

xEventEntry.name: xEventEntry
xEventEntry.description: Parameter values for a event entry.

xEventIndex.name: xEventIndex
xEventIndex.description: In identification number for an event. The value 1 indicates the oldest event in the file, with subsequent numbers indicating sequential events. The event text for a given number may change as a circular event log wraps over its beginning. Corresponds directly to the relative position of an event in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

xEventText.name: xEventText
xEventText.description: The text of the event, including date, time and other information. Corresponds directly to the individual event text in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

basicDeviceNumber.name: basicDeviceNumber
basicDeviceNumber.description: The system's number of mass-storage devices.

deviceTable.name: deviceTable
deviceTable.description: A list of device entries. The number of entries is given by basicDeviceNumber.

deviceEntry.name: deviceEntry
deviceEntry.description: Parameter values for a device entry.

deviceIndex.name: deviceIndex
deviceIndex.description: In identification number for a device, in the range 1 to basicDeviceNumber

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: A name by which the device is known in other displays, such as 'C1' or 'D2'.

deviceDescr.name: deviceDescr
deviceDescr.description: Details of the device type, including, for example, size, manufacturer, Flash versus RAM, and such. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Device Type: in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceOperation.name: deviceOperation
deviceOperation.description: Current operational state of the device. Corresponds directly the value labeled 'Device Operation:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceFormat.name: deviceFormat
deviceFormat.description: Formatting status of the device. Corresponds directly the presence of one of the value labels under the label 'Device Status:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceProtection.name: deviceProtection
deviceProtection.description: Write-protect status of the device. Corresponds directly the presence of one of the value labels under the label 'Device Status:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceFormatMedium.name: deviceFormatMedium
deviceFormatMedium.description: Control to cause formatting of the medium in the device. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the device to be formatted. Corresponds directly to the FORMAT DEVICE command.

deviceGetFile.name: deviceGetFile
deviceGetFile.description: Control to cause getting a file to the device from a remote host system. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the get to be attempted. Corresponds directly to the GET DEVICE command. When set to 'execute', the objects deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType, deviceGetFileHostIdentification, deviceGetFileName and deviceGetFileArea must be somewhere in the same set request message.

deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType.name: deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType
deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in deviceIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to ADDRESS in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is 'undefined'.

deviceGetFileHostIdentification.name: deviceGetFileHostIdentification
deviceGetFileHostIdentification.description: Identification of the host to get the file from, with type depending on deviceIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to ADDRESS in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero length.

deviceGetFileName.name: deviceGetFileName
deviceGetFileName.description: The name of the file to get. Corresponds directly to LOAD FILE in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero length.

deviceGetFileArea.name: deviceGetFileArea
deviceGetFileArea.description: The area number in which to put the file. Corresponds directly to AREA in the GET DEVICE command. If it is not relevant to the particular device, it is ignored. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero.

deviceFormatOption.name: deviceFormatOption
deviceFormatOption.description: Formatting option to apply. Corresponds directly to the OPTION in the FORMAT DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceFormatMedium to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero.

deviceFormatRedundantParams.name: deviceFormatRedundantParams
deviceFormatRedundantParams.description: Control for creating redundant parameter storage areas when formatting. Corresponds directly to NONREDUNDANT in the FORMAT DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceFormatMedium to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero.

devicePreviousStatus.name: devicePreviousStatus
devicePreviousStatus.description: Result of the immediately previous concluded boot dialog. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Get File Previous Status:' in the SHOW CARD STATUS display.

dumpService.name: dumpService
dumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for any client. Corresponds directly to DUMP and the value labeled 'Dump:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpDrive.name: dumpDrive
dumpDrive.description: Identification number of the disk drive where dumps are stored. Corresponds directly to DUMP DRIVE and the value labeled 'Dump Drive:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpMerit.name: dumpMerit
dumpMerit.description: Relative preference for this dump server over others. Corresponds directly to DUMP MERIT and the value labeled 'Dump Merit:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpSize.name: dumpSize
dumpSize.description: Type of dump file to keep. Corresponds directly to DUMP SIZE and the value labeled 'Dump Size:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpCompleted.name: dumpCompleted
dumpCompleted.description: The number of dumps completed since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump Operations Completed:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

dumpActive.name: dumpActive
dumpActive.description: The number of dumps in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Dumping:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

dumpFileNumber.name: dumpFileNumber
dumpFileNumber.description: The number of dump files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Network dump files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileTable.name: dumpFileTable
dumpFileTable.description: A list of dump file entries. The number of entries is given by dumpFileNumber.

dumpFileEntry.name: dumpFileEntry
dumpFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a dump file entry.

dumpFileIdentificationType.name: dumpFileIdentificationType
dumpFileIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in dumpFileIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileIdentification.name: dumpFileIdentification
dumpFileIdentification.description: Identification of the dump file, an Ethernet address, as indicated by dumpFileIdentificationType. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileEntryStatus.name: dumpFileEntryStatus
dumpFileEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds indirectly to the PURGE MANAGER DUMP FILES command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

dumpFileCreation.name: dumpFileCreation
dumpFileCreation.description: The time the dump file was created. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileSize.name: dumpFileSize
dumpFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the dump file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadService.name: loadService
loadService.description: Control for allowing load service for any client. Corresponds directly to LOAD and the value labeled 'Load:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

loadMerit.name: loadMerit
loadMerit.description: Relative preference for this load server over others. Corresponds directly to LOAD MERIT and the value labeled 'Load Merit:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

loadCompleted.name: loadCompleted
loadCompleted.description: The number of loads completed since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load Operations Completed:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

loadActive.name: loadActive
loadActive.description: The number of loads in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Loading:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

loadFileNumber.name: loadFileNumber
loadFileNumber.description: The number of load files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load image files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileTable.name: loadFileTable
loadFileTable.description: A list of load file entries. The number of entries is given by loadFileNumber.

loadFileEntry.name: loadFileEntry
loadFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a load file entry.

loadFileName.name: loadFileName
loadFileName.description: The name of a load file. Corresponds directly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileCreation.name: loadFileCreation
loadFileCreation.description: The time the load file was created. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileSize.name: loadFileSize
loadFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the load file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileSoftwareVersionType.name: loadFileSoftwareVersionType
loadFileSoftwareVersionType.description: The software version type of the image in the load file. Corresponds directly to a software version in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display. alpha 'A': alpha test beta 'B': beta test production null: normal, production software special 'S': special, custom software

loadFileSoftwareVersion.name: loadFileSoftwareVersion
loadFileSoftwareVersion.description: The software version of the image in the load file. Corresponds directly to a software version in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display. For example, the version display for loadFileSoftwareVersionType 'production' and loadFileSoftwareVersion '2.2.0.0' is 'V2.2'. The version display for loadFileSoftwareVersionType 'beta' and loadFileSoftwareVersion '3.1.0.4' is 'V3.1B4'.

paramService.name: paramService
paramService.description: Control for allowing parameter storage service for any client. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVICE and the value labeled 'Parameter Service:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramDefaultService.name: paramDefaultService
paramDefaultService.description: Control for allowing default parameter loading service for any client. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER DEFAULT SERVICE and the value labeled 'Parameter Default Service:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramDrive.name: paramDrive
paramDrive.description: Identification number of the disk drive where parameters are stored. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER DRIVE and the value labeled 'Parameter Drive:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramActive.name: paramActive
paramActive.description: The number of params in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Paraming:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

paramStorageActive.name: paramStorageActive
paramStorageActive.description: The number of parameter storage operations in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently saving parameters:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

paramFileNumber.name: paramFileNumber
paramFileNumber.description: The number of parameter files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Parameter files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileTable.name: paramFileTable
paramFileTable.description: A list of param file entries. The number of entries is given by paramFileNumber.

paramFileEntry.name: paramFileEntry
paramFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a param file entry.

paramFileIdentificationType.name: paramFileIdentificationType
paramFileIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in paramFileIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileIdentification.name: paramFileIdentification
paramFileIdentification.description: Identification of the param file, an Ethernet address, as indicated by paramFileIdentificationType. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileEntryStatus.name: paramFileEntryStatus
paramFileEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds indirectly to the PURGE MANAGER PARAMETER FILES command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

paramFileWrite.name: paramFileWrite
paramFileWrite.description: The time the parameter file was last written. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileSize.name: paramFileSize
paramFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the param file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileParameterVersion.name: paramFileParameterVersion
paramFileParameterVersion.description: The version number of the parameter data in the file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'ver' in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

basicBase802Address.name: basicBase802Address
basicBase802Address.description: Base IEEE 802 global address for the chassis.

basicSlot.name: basicSlot
basicSlot.description: Chassis slot number (slotIndex) of the system whose agent is supplying this MIB.

basicSlotNumber.name: basicSlotNumber
basicSlotNumber.description: Number of slots in the chassis.

basicNewBase802Address.name: basicNewBase802Address
basicNewBase802Address.description: New base IEEE 802 global address for the chassis. Must be set in conjunction with featType 'changeEthernetAddress' and featKey from the MRV In-Reach System MIB.

segmentTable.name: segmentTable
segmentTable.description: A list of segment entries, one for each segment of each type on the chassis.

segmentIndex.name: segmentIndex
segmentIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a segment.

portIOCardType.name: portIOCardType
portIOCardType.description: The hardware type of the I/O card in this slot.

portIOCardSerialNumber.name: portIOCardSerialNumber
portIOCardSerialNumber.description: The MRV In-Reach serial number of the I/O card in this slot.

portIOCardOperStatus.name: portIOCardOperStatus
portIOCardOperStatus.description: Status of the I/O card relative to the function card in this slot.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: A list of port entries, one for each port of each type on the slots I/O card.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: Values for an I/O card port.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port.

controllerTable.name: controllerTable
controllerTable.description: A list of controller entries, one for each controller of each type on the local system.

controllerIndex.name: controllerIndex
controllerIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a controller.

controllerNetwork.name: controllerNetwork
controllerNetwork.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the segment, port, or controller this controller is to use, that is, segmentType, portType or controllerType.

interfaceTable.name: interfaceTable
interfaceTable.description: A list of interface entries, corresponding to the MIB II Interface group. These are directly equivalent to hardware network controllers, and must be the lowest numbered interfaces on the system.

interfaceIndex.name: interfaceIndex
interfaceIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

interfaceNetwork.name: interfaceNetwork
interfaceNetwork.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the segment, port, or controller this interface is to use, that is, segmentType, portType, or controllerType.

slotBootControlTable.name: slotBootControlTable
slotBootControlTable.description: A list of slot boot control entries.

slotBootControlSlot.name: slotBootControlSlot
slotBootControlSlot.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a slot, defined the same as slotIndex.

slotBootControlIndex.name: slotBootControlIndex
slotBootControlIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a boot control entry, from 1 to the number of entries for the slot.

slotBootControlStatus.name: slotBootControlStatus
slotBootControlStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'disabled' to disable the entry.

slotBootControlController.name: slotBootControlController
slotBootControlController.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the controller this entry selects for bootstrap operation, that is, controllerType. This entry must be compatible with slotBootControlNetwork, including being of the same network type. The value 0.0 indicates default action.

slotBootControlNetwork.name: slotBootControlNetwork
slotBootControlNetwork.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the segment or port this entry selects for bootstrap operation, that is, segmentType or portType. This entry must be compatible with slotBootControlController, including being of the same network type. The value 0.0 indicates default action.

slotBootControlMopFile.name: slotBootControlMopFile
slotBootControlMopFile.description: The software file name to request for down-line load of the server via MOP or XMOP.

slotBootControlInternetFile.name: slotBootControlInternetFile
slotBootControlInternetFile.description: The filename to request when loading an image via TFTP.

slotBootControlInternetAddress.name: slotBootControlInternetAddress
slotBootControlInternetAddress.description: The internet address of the system is to use for itself when loading via TFTP. The value 0.0.0.0 indicates default action.

slotBootControlInternetServer.name: slotBootControlInternetServer
slotBootControlInternetServer.description: The internet address of the server to use when loading an image via TFTP. The value 0.0.0.0 indicates default action.

slotBootControlInternetGateway.name: slotBootControlInternetGateway
slotBootControlInternetGateway.description: The internet address of the gateway to use when loading an image via TFTP. The value 0.0.0.0 indicates default action.

slotBootControlInternetDelimiter.name: slotBootControlInternetDelimiter
slotBootControlInternetDelimiter.description: The character separating the load file directory name from the file name.

slotBootControlFlagTable.name: slotBootControlFlagTable
slotBootControlFlagTable.description: A list of slot boot control source flag entries.

slotBootControlFlagEntry.name: slotBootControlFlagEntry
slotBootControlFlagEntry.description: Values for a boot control flag.

slotBootControlFlagLoadBootpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadBootpTftp
slotBootControlFlagLoadBootpTftp.description: Control for performing load over BOOTP/TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagParamBootpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagParamBootpTftp
slotBootControlFlagParamBootpTftp.description: Control for performing parameter load over BOOTP/TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagDumpBootpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpBootpTftp
slotBootControlFlagDumpBootpTftp.description: Control for performing dump over BOOTP/TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagLoadTftpDirect.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadTftpDirect
slotBootControlFlagLoadTftpDirect.description: Control for performing load over direct TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagParamTftpDirect.name: slotBootControlFlagParamTftpDirect
slotBootControlFlagParamTftpDirect.description: Control for performing parameter load over direct TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagDumpTftpDirect.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpTftpDirect
slotBootControlFlagDumpTftpDirect.description: Control for performing dump over direct TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagLoadLocal.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadLocal
slotBootControlFlagLoadLocal.description: Control for performing load from a local device.

slotBootControlFlagParamLocal.name: slotBootControlFlagParamLocal
slotBootControlFlagParamLocal.description: Control for performing parameter load from a local device.

slotBootControlFlagDumpLocal.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpLocal
slotBootControlFlagDumpLocal.description: Control for performing dump from a local device.

slotBootControlFlagLoadMop.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadMop
slotBootControlFlagLoadMop.description: Control for performing load over Digital's MOP.

slotBootControlFlagParamMop.name: slotBootControlFlagParamMop
slotBootControlFlagParamMop.description: Control for performing parameter load over Digital's MOP.

slotBootControlFlagDumpMop.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpMop
slotBootControlFlagDumpMop.description: Control for performing dump over Digital's MOP.

slotBootControlFlagLoadXmop.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadXmop
slotBootControlFlagLoadXmop.description: Control for performing load over MRV In-Reach extended MOP.

slotBootControlFlagParamXmop.name: slotBootControlFlagParamXmop
slotBootControlFlagParamXmop.description: Control for performing parameter load over MRV In-Reach extended MOP.

slotBootControlFlagDumpXmop.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpXmop
slotBootControlFlagDumpXmop.description: Control for performing dump over MRV In-Reach extended MOP.

slotBootControlFlagLoadRarpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagLoadRarpTftp
slotBootControlFlagLoadRarpTftp.description: Control for performing load over RARP/TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagParamRarpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagParamRarpTftp
slotBootControlFlagParamRarpTftp.description: Control for performing parameter load over RARP/TFTP.

slotBootControlFlagDumpRarpTftp.name: slotBootControlFlagDumpRarpTftp
slotBootControlFlagDumpRarpTftp.description: Control for performing dump over RARP/TFTP.

slotBootControlStorageTable.name: slotBootControlStorageTable
slotBootControlStorageTable.description: A list of slot boot control Storage entries.

slotBootControlStorageClientSlot.name: slotBootControlStorageClientSlot
slotBootControlStorageClientSlot.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a slot, defined the same as slotIndex.

slotBootControlStorageServerSlot.name: slotBootControlStorageServerSlot
slotBootControlStorageServerSlot.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the slot in which the Storage record resides, with the same values as slotIndex.

slotBootControlStorageFailures.name: slotBootControlStorageFailures
slotBootControlStorageFailures.description: The number of times a read from or write to a given Storage location failed

slotIndex.name: slotIndex
slotIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a slot, in the range 0 to basicSlotNumber, where the value 0 indicates the same slot as basicSlot. As the objects found at instance zero are duplicates, that instance does not appear in responses a get-next, that is, the lowest numbered slotIndex returned by get-next is 1.

slotAdminAction.name: slotAdminAction
slotAdminAction.description: Control to cause reset of the system in a slot. When read, the value is always 'ready'. Setting to 'reset' or 'resetHold' causes a single attempt to take that action, but does not ensure transition to any particular value of slotOperStatus.

slotOperStatus.name: slotOperStatus
slotOperStatus.description: Relative to the chassis, the current operating status of the system in the slot.

slotSecondsSinceReset.name: slotSecondsSinceReset
slotSecondsSinceReset.description: The number of seconds since the system in the slot was last reset by hardware or software.

slotHardwareType.name: slotHardwareType
slotHardwareType.description: The type of hardware in the slot.

slotHardwareSerialNumber.name: slotHardwareSerialNumber
slotHardwareSerialNumber.description: The MRV In-Reach serial number of the function card hardware in this slot.

slotHardwareRevision.name: slotHardwareRevision
slotHardwareRevision.description: This revision level of the function card hardware in the slot.

slotIOCardType.name: slotIOCardType
slotIOCardType.description: The hardware type of the I/O card in this slot.

slotIOCardSerialNumber.name: slotIOCardSerialNumber
slotIOCardSerialNumber.description: The MRV In-Reach serial number of the I/O card in this slot.

slotIOCardOperStatus.name: slotIOCardOperStatus
slotIOCardOperStatus.description: Status of the I/O card relative to the function card in this slot.

slotBootstrapFirmwareRevision.name: slotBootstrapFirmwareRevision
slotBootstrapFirmwareRevision.description: The firmware revision level of the bootstrap ROM installed in the system in the slot.

slotElementalFirmwareRevision.name: slotElementalFirmwareRevision
slotElementalFirmwareRevision.description: The firmware revision level of the minimal function ROM (management bus microprocessor) installed in the system in the slot.

slotMemorySize.name: slotMemorySize
slotMemorySize.description: The number of bytes of memory installed in the system in the slot.

slotLedNumber.name: slotLedNumber
slotLedNumber.description: The number of LEDs on the system in the slot. A value of 0 indicates none, unknown, or status not readable.

slotLedStatus.name: slotLedStatus
slotLedStatus.description: The status of the LEDs displayed on the front and back of the system in the slot. The first bit is the high-order bit of the first byte of the value, proceeding to the low-order bit, then to then next byte. On the system hardware, the first LED is at the top, left, front, proceeding left to right, top to bottom, and front to back.

slotBase802Address.name: slotBase802Address
slotBase802Address.description: Base IEEE 802 global address for the slot.

slotIpAddress.name: slotIpAddress
slotIpAddress.description: An internet address to which the system in this slot might respond. May be one of many.

slotPlus5Status.name: slotPlus5Status
slotPlus5Status.description: Status of the +5 volt power to the slot.

slotPlus12Status.name: slotPlus12Status
slotPlus12Status.description: Status of the +12 volt power to the slot.

slotMinus12Status.name: slotMinus12Status
slotMinus12Status.description: Status of the -12 volt power to the slot.

slotPlus5Watts.name: slotPlus5Watts
slotPlus5Watts.description: Tenths of watts of +5 volt power currently drawn by the slot.

slotPlus12Watts.name: slotPlus12Watts
slotPlus12Watts.description: Tenths of watts of +12 volt power currently drawn by the slot.

slotMinus12Watts.name: slotMinus12Watts
slotMinus12Watts.description: Tenths of watts of -12 volt power currently drawn by the slot.

slotIOCardHardwareVersion.name: slotIOCardHardwareVersion
slotIOCardHardwareVersion.description: Version number of I/O card in the slot.

slotRestoreNVS.name: slotRestoreNVS
slotRestoreNVS.description: Setting to 'execute' causes the non-volatile parameter storage to be restored from an installed memory card. Setting to 'ready' has no effect.

slotDefaultNVS.name: slotDefaultNVS
slotDefaultNVS.description: Setting to 'execute' causes non-volatile stored parameters to be reset to factory defaults. Setting to 'ready' has no effect.

slotBootTable.name: slotBootTable
slotBootTable.description: A list of slot bootstrap status entries. A given slot has an entry in this table only when slotOperStatus is one of: loadRequested, loading, dumpRequested, dumping, paramRequested, paramLoading

slotBootEntry.name: slotBootEntry
slotBootEntry.description: Bootstrap status values for a chassis slot.

slotBootIndex.name: slotBootIndex
slotBootIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a slot, defined the same as slotIndex.

slotBootIfIndex.name: slotBootIfIndex
slotBootIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies the interface in use for bootstrap functions. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

slotBootNetwork.name: slotBootNetwork
slotBootNetwork.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the segment or port this interface is using, that is, segmentType or portType.

slotBootProtocol.name: slotBootProtocol
slotBootProtocol.description: The protocol in use for bootstrap operation.

slotBoot802Address.name: slotBoot802Address
slotBoot802Address.description: IEEE 802 global address in use for bootstrap operation.

slotBootAddressType.name: slotBootAddressType
slotBootAddressType.description: The type of network address contained in slotBootAddress.

slotBootAddress.name: slotBootAddress
slotBootAddress.description: The network address the system in the slot is using to identify itself for bootstrap operation.

slotBootServerAddressType.name: slotBootServerAddressType
slotBootServerAddressType.description: The type of network address contained in slotBootServerAddress.

slotBootServerAddress.name: slotBootServerAddress
slotBootServerAddress.description: The network address of the system supplying bootstrap services to the system in the slot.

slotBootGatewayAddress.name: slotBootGatewayAddress
slotBootGatewayAddress.description: The internet address of the router in use for bootstrap operation.

slotBootFileName.name: slotBootFileName
slotBootFileName.description: The full name of the file in use for bootstrap operation.

slotBootBlockNumber.name: slotBootBlockNumber
slotBootBlockNumber.description: The current block number being transferred for bootstrap operation, zero if unknown or not applicable.

slotBootCrashCode.name: slotBootCrashCode
slotBootCrashCode.description: If slotOperStatus is dumpRequested or dumping, a code number to identify the crash reason; otherwise zero length.

slotControllerTable.name: slotControllerTable
slotControllerTable.description: A list of controller entries, one for each controller of each type in each slot.

slotControllerIndex.name: slotControllerIndex
slotControllerIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a controller.

slotControllerNetwork.name: slotControllerNetwork
slotControllerNetwork.description: The instance identifier of the first object in the conceptual row entry for the segment or port this controller is to use, that is, segmentType or portType.

powerSupplyTable.name: powerSupplyTable
powerSupplyTable.description: A list of power supply entries.

powerSupplyEntry.name: powerSupplyEntry
powerSupplyEntry.description: Values for a chassis power supply.

powerSupplyIndex.name: powerSupplyIndex
powerSupplyIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a power supply, in the range 1 to the number of power supply slots in the chassis.

powerSupplyAdminAction.name: powerSupplyAdminAction
powerSupplyAdminAction.description: Control to cause reset of the power supply. When read, the value is always 'ready'. Setting to 'reset' or 'resetHold' causes a single attempt to take that action, but does not ensure transition to any particular value of powerSupplyRedundancyStatus.

powerSupplyFirmwareVersion.name: powerSupplyFirmwareVersion
powerSupplyFirmwareVersion.description: Version number of power supply firmware.

powerSupplyRedundancyStatus.name: powerSupplyRedundancyStatus
powerSupplyRedundancyStatus.description: The current redundancy status of the power supply.

powerSupplyPlus5Status.name: powerSupplyPlus5Status
powerSupplyPlus5Status.description: Status of the +5 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyPlus12Status.name: powerSupplyPlus12Status
powerSupplyPlus12Status.description: Status of the +12 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyMinus12Status.name: powerSupplyMinus12Status
powerSupplyMinus12Status.description: Status of the -12 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyThermalWarningStatus.name: powerSupplyThermalWarningStatus
powerSupplyThermalWarningStatus.description: The current thermal warning status of the power supply.

powerSupplyThermalShutdownStatus.name: powerSupplyThermalShutdownStatus
powerSupplyThermalShutdownStatus.description: The current thermal shutdown status of the power supply.

powerSupplyFanStatus.name: powerSupplyFanStatus
powerSupplyFanStatus.description: The current status of the power supply's fan.

powerSupplyHardwareInhibitStatus.name: powerSupplyHardwareInhibitStatus
powerSupplyHardwareInhibitStatus.description: The current status of the power supply's hardware inhibit.

powerSupplyPlus5History.name: powerSupplyPlus5History
powerSupplyPlus5History.description: History of the +5 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyPlus12History.name: powerSupplyPlus12History
powerSupplyPlus12History.description: History of the +12 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyMinus12History.name: powerSupplyMinus12History
powerSupplyMinus12History.description: History of the -12 volt power from the power supply.

powerSupplyThermalWarningHistory.name: powerSupplyThermalWarningHistory
powerSupplyThermalWarningHistory.description: The thermal warning history of the power supply.

powerSupplyThermalShutdownHistory.name: powerSupplyThermalShutdownHistory
powerSupplyThermalShutdownHistory.description: The thermal shutdown history of the power supply.

powerSupplyFanHistory.name: powerSupplyFanHistory
powerSupplyFanHistory.description: The status history of the power supply's fan.

powerSupplyHardwareInhibitHistory.name: powerSupplyHardwareInhibitHistory
powerSupplyHardwareInhibitHistory.description: The status history of the power supply's hardware inhibit.

powerSupplyPlus5Volts.name: powerSupplyPlus5Volts
powerSupplyPlus5Volts.description: In hundredths, volts of +5 volt power currently provided by the power supply. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyPlus12Volts.name: powerSupplyPlus12Volts
powerSupplyPlus12Volts.description: In hundredths, volts of +12 volt power currently provided by the power supply. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyMinus12Volts.name: powerSupplyMinus12Volts
powerSupplyMinus12Volts.description: In hundredths, volts of -12 volt power currently provided by the power supply. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyWatts.name: powerSupplyWatts
powerSupplyWatts.description: Watts of power currently drawn from this power supply. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyWattsMax.name: powerSupplyWattsMax
powerSupplyWattsMax.description: Maximum watts of power available from this power supply. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyChassisWatts.name: powerSupplyChassisWatts
powerSupplyChassisWatts.description: Total watts of power currently drawn by the entire chassis. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

powerSupplyChassisWattsMax.name: powerSupplyChassisWattsMax
powerSupplyChassisWattsMax.description: Total maximum watts of power available from all the power supplies in the chassis. A value of 0 indicates unknown.

firmwareUpdateTable.name: firmwareUpdateTable
firmwareUpdateTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information concerning the writing of firmware to a target I/O card.

firmwareUpdateEntry.name: firmwareUpdateEntry
firmwareUpdateEntry.description: An entry in the table concerning the writing of firmware to a target I/O card.

firmwareUpdateSlotIndex.name: firmwareUpdateSlotIndex
firmwareUpdateSlotIndex.description: This variable identifies the slot to which is to be the target of the firmware update.

firmwareUpdateDefaultFileName.name: firmwareUpdateDefaultFileName
firmwareUpdateDefaultFileName.description: This variable when read will obtain the default file name from the target.

firmwareUpdateFileName.name: firmwareUpdateFileName
firmwareUpdateFileName.description: This variable contains the name of the file to be read from the flash memory card and written to the target.

firmwareUpdateStatus.name: firmwareUpdateStatus
firmwareUpdateStatus.description: This variable is used to start the update process. The agent always 'ready' for this value. Setting this value to 'execute' causes the agent to write the file specified by firmwareUpdateFileName to be written to the taget. Setting this value to 'execute' when firmwareUpdateFileName has not been written or when firmwareUpdateState is 'writing' causes bad value to be returned.

firmwareUpdateState.name: firmwareUpdateState
firmwareUpdateState.description: This variable indicates the current state of firmware update, 'idle' indicates that firmware update may be initiated, and 'writing' indicates that an update is in process.

firmwareUpdateCompletionStatus.name: firmwareUpdateCompletionStatus
firmwareUpdateCompletionStatus.description: This variable indicates the completion status of the the last firmware update attempt. 'none' indicates that no firmware update has yet been attempted.

firmwareUpdateMethod.name: firmwareUpdateMethod
firmwareUpdateMethod.description: This variable indicates the method of update of the firmware update attempt.

basicBroadcast.name: basicBroadcast
basicBroadcast.description: Control for user ability to broadcast messages to other local ports. Corresponds directly to SERVER BROADCAST and the presence of the label 'Broadcast' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicErrorReport.name: basicErrorReport
basicErrorReport.description: Control for server display of an error when the user gives an unsupported command. Corresponds directly to SERVER REPORT ERRORS and the presence of the label 'Report Errors' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicLock.name: basicLock
basicLock.description: Control for user ability to use a password to protect a logged in terminal from other users. Corresponds directly to SERVER LOCK and the presence of the label 'Lock' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicInactivityTimer.name: basicInactivityTimer
basicInactivityTimer.description: Number of minutes a terminal may remain logged in with no sessions, no input or output, and no modem transitions. Corresponds directly to SERVER INACTIVITY TIMER and the value labeled 'Inactivity Timer:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicPasswordRetryLimit.name: basicPasswordRetryLimit
basicPasswordRetryLimit.description: Number of times the server allows a user to retry an incorrect password. Corresponds directly to SERVER PASSWORD LIMIT and the value labeled 'Password Limit:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicPrivilegedPassword.name: basicPrivilegedPassword
basicPrivilegedPassword.description: The password a user must enter to become privileged. For security reasons, reading this object always returns a zero-length value. Corresponds directly to SERVER PRIVILEGED PASSWORD.

basicLoginPassword.name: basicLoginPassword
basicLoginPassword.description: The password a user must enter to be given the opportunity to log in. For security reasons, reading this object always returns a zero-length value. Corresponds directly to SERVER LOGIN PASSWORD.

basicLoginPrompt.name: basicLoginPrompt
basicLoginPrompt.description: The text string the server displays to prompt a user for the login password. Corresponds directly to SERVER LOGIN PROMPT.

basicWelcome.name: basicWelcome
basicWelcome.description: The text string the server displays before attempting to log in a user. Corresponds directly to SERVER WELCOME and the value labeled 'Welcome:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicActivePorts.name: basicActivePorts
basicActivePorts.description: The number of ports with connected sessions or logged in users. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Active Ports:' and 'Cur' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicActivePortsHigh.name: basicActivePortsHigh
basicActivePortsHigh.description: The highest value of basicActivePorts since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Active Ports:' and 'High' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicActiveUsers.name: basicActiveUsers
basicActiveUsers.description: The number of logged in users. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Active Users:' and 'Cur' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicActiveUsersHigh.name: basicActiveUsersHigh
basicActiveUsersHigh.description: The highest value of basicActiveUsers since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Active Users:' and 'High' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicSessions.name: basicSessions
basicSessions.description: The total number of connected sessions. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Connected Sessions:' and 'Cur' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicSessionsHigh.name: basicSessionsHigh
basicSessionsHigh.description: The highest value of basicSessions since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Connected Sessions:' and 'High' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicSessionsLimit.name: basicSessionsLimit
basicSessionsLimit.description: The maximum total number of sessions that can simultaneously be connected to the system. A value of -1 indicates no limit up to available dynamic system memory. Corresponds directly to SERVER SESSION LIMIT and the value labeled 'Connected Sessions:' and 'Max' in the SERVER STATUS display.

basicPortTable.name: basicPortTable
basicPortTable.description: A list of basic character port entries.

basicPortEntry.name: basicPortEntry
basicPortEntry.description: Basic parameter values for a port.

basicPortIndex.name: basicPortIndex
basicPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the standard Character MIB.

basicPortDefaultDestAction.name: basicPortDefaultDestAction
