tn3270ScreenStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table.

tn3270ScreenCharacterSequence.name: tn3270ScreenCharacterSequence
tn3270ScreenCharacterSequence.description: The ASCII character sequence for the screen action. Some actions may have a lesser length limit. Corresponds directly to the escape-sequence portion of SERVER TN3270 DEVICE SCREENMAP and the value labeled 'HexCode' in the 'Screenmap: section of the SERVER TN3270 DEVICE display.

tn3270LanguageTable.name: tn3270LanguageTable
tn3270LanguageTable.description: A list of tn3270 language entries.

tn3270LanguageEntry.name: tn3270LanguageEntry
tn3270LanguageEntry.description: Tn3270 parameter values for a language entry.

tn3270LanguageName.name: tn3270LanguageName
tn3270LanguageName.description: The name of language for character translation tables. Corresponds directly to SERVER TN3270 LANGUAGE and the value labeled 'Language Name:' in the SERVER LANGUAGE display.

tn3270LanguageStatus.name: tn3270LanguageStatus
tn3270LanguageStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. If a new device table entry is added to the table, the agent will copy the USENGLSH table as the default.

eToALanguageTable.name: eToALanguageTable
eToALanguageTable.description: A list of language EBCDIC to ASCII conversion entries.

eToALanguageEntry.name: eToALanguageEntry
eToALanguageEntry.description: EBCDIC to ASCII parameter values for a language entry.

eToALanguageName.name: eToALanguageName
eToALanguageName.description: The name of language from the language table.

eToAOffset.name: eToAOffset
eToAOffset.description: EBCDIC character offset plus one, that is, the value 1 corresponds to an operational offset of 0. Corresponds directly to the offset portion of SERVER TN3270 LANGUAGE and the hexadecimal labels around the conversion table labeled 'EBCDIC to ASCII' in the SERVER LANGUAGE display.

eToAValue.name: eToAValue
eToAValue.description: ASCII character value for the EBCDIC offset. Corresponds directly to the value portion of SERVER TN3270 LANGUAGE and the values in the conversion table labeled 'EBCDIC to ASCII' in the SERVER LANGUAGE display.

aToELanguageTable.name: aToELanguageTable
aToELanguageTable.description: A list of language ASCII to EBCDIC conversion entries.

aToELanguageEntry.name: aToELanguageEntry
aToELanguageEntry.description: ASCII to EBCDIC parameter values for a language entry.

aToELanguageName.name: aToELanguageName
aToELanguageName.description: The name of language from the language table.

aToEOffset.name: aToEOffset
aToEOffset.description: ASCII character offset plus one, that is, the value 1 corresponds to an operational offset of 0. Corresponds directly to the offset portion of SERVER TN3270 LANGUAGE and the hexadecimal labels around the conversion table labeled 'ASCII to EBCDIC' in the SERVER LANGUAGE display.

aToEValue.name: aToEValue
aToEValue.description: EBCDIC character value for the ASCII offset. Corresponds directly to the value portion of SERVER TN3270 LANGUAGE and the values in the conversion table labeled 'ASCII to EBCDIC' in the SERVER LANGUAGE display.

tn3270PortTable.name: tn3270PortTable
tn3270PortTable.description: A list of tn3270 character port entries.

tn3270PortEntry.name: tn3270PortEntry
tn3270PortEntry.description: Parameter values for a tn3270 port.

tn3270PortIndex.name: tn3270PortIndex
tn3270PortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

tn3270PortDeviceName.name: tn3270PortDeviceName
tn3270PortDeviceName.description: The name of a generic terminal device from the tn3270 device table. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 DEVICE and the value labeled 'Tn3270 Device:' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortLanguageName.name: tn3270PortLanguageName
tn3270PortLanguageName.description: The name of language from the tn3270 language table. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 LANGUAGE and the value labeled 'Tn3270 Language:' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortExtendedAttributes.name: tn3270PortExtendedAttributes
tn3270PortExtendedAttributes.description: A control indicating that certain 3270 extended attributes are supported on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 XTDATTRS and the label 'Tn3270 XtdAttrs' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortEorNegotiation.name: tn3270PortEorNegotiation
tn3270PortEorNegotiation.description: A control for negotiation of the Telnet EOR option when establishing a tn3270 session on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 EOR and the label 'Tn3270 EOR' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortErrorLock.name: tn3270PortErrorLock
tn3270PortErrorLock.description: A control for requiring use the RESET key when the host reports an error during a tn3270 session on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 ERRORLOCK and the label 'Tn3270 ErrorLock' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortPrinterPort.name: tn3270PortPrinterPort
tn3270PortPrinterPort.description: The port number of the tn3270 printer. Corresponds directly to PORT TELNET TN3270 PRINTER and the value labeled 'Tn3270 Printer:' in the PORT TELNET display.

tn3270PortOutgoingTcpPort.name: tn3270PortOutgoingTcpPort
tn3270PortOutgoingTcpPort.description: The TCP port which is used for a TN3270 session when connecting to a remote host from this serial port. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Tn3270 Default Port:' in the PORT TELNET CHARACTERISTICS display.

tn3270PortSpaceInsert.name: tn3270PortSpaceInsert
tn3270PortSpaceInsert.description: Control to allow insert mode within a space filled field, and write characters over EBCDIC spaces. Corresponds directly to the presence of 'Tn3270 Space_Insert' under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET CHARACTERISTICS display.

tn3270PortTypeAhead.name: tn3270PortTypeAhead
tn3270PortTypeAhead.description: Control to permit typing ahead in a tn3270 session prior to receiving a response from the host for the previous command entered. Corresponds directly to the presence of 'Tn3270 TypeAhead' under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET CHARACTERISTICS display.

tn3270PrefixKeyMap.name: tn3270PrefixKeyMap
tn3270PrefixKeyMap.description: Control to prepend a prefix function to another function key. When the operator hits the key the prepended function(s) and then the main function for the key are transmitted to the host. Corresponds directly to the presence of 'Tn3270 PrefixKeyMap' under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET CHARACTERISTICS display.

tn3270PortScanner.name: tn3270PortScanner
tn3270PortScanner.description: Indicates that this is a tn3270 scanner port. Corresponds directly to the presence of 'Tn3270 SCANNER' under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT TELNET CHARACTERISTICS display.

kerbStatus.name: kerbStatus
kerbStatus.description: A control indicating the level of Kerberos operation on the system. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS STATUS and the value labeled 'Kerberos Security:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbRealm.name: kerbRealm
kerbRealm.description: The Kerberos realm with which the kerbServerName1 and kerbServerName2 are associated. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS REALM and the value labeled 'Kerberos Realm:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbQueryLimit.name: kerbQueryLimit
kerbQueryLimit.description: The maximum number of attempts the system can make when trying to verify a Kerberos ID. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS QUERY LIMIT and the value labeled 'Kerberos Query Limit:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbMasterName.name: kerbMasterName
kerbMasterName.description: The Domain name of the Kerberos master host system, which holds the Kerberos database. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS MASTER and the value labeled 'Kerberos Master:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerName1.name: kerbServerName1
kerbServerName1.description: The Domain name of the first Kerberos server to try when the system verifys a Kerberos ID. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS PRIMARY SERVER and the value labeled 'Kerberos Primary Server:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerName2.name: kerbServerName2
kerbServerName2.description: The Domain name of the Kerberos server to try when the system verifys a Kerberos ID and cannot reach the Kerberos primary server. Corresponds directly to SERVER KERBEROS SECONDARY SERVER and the value labeled 'Kerberos Secondary Server:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbInsecureLogins.name: kerbInsecureLogins
kerbInsecureLogins.description: The number of user logins on ports for which Kerberos user verification is not enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Logins without Kerberos:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbSecureLogins.name: kerbSecureLogins
kerbSecureLogins.description: The number of successful user logins on ports for which Kerberos user verification is enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Successful Logins:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbSecureLoginsFailed.name: kerbSecureLoginsFailed
kerbSecureLoginsFailed.description: The number of verification failures due to incorrect ID or password for attempted user logins on ports for which Kerberos user verification is enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Unsuccessful Logins:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbPasswordChangeFailed.name: kerbPasswordChangeFailed
kerbPasswordChangeFailed.description: The number of user failures to change their Kerberos password due to invalid old password or new password verification. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Password Change Failures:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbError.name: kerbError
kerbError.description: The error number of the most recent Kerberos-related failure. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Last Kerberos Error:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display. For a list of error numbers and their meanings, consult relevant MRV In-Reach or Kerberos documentation.

kerbErrorTime.name: kerbErrorTime
kerbErrorTime.description: The date and time that kerbError was last updated. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Occurred:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbMasterAccess.name: kerbMasterAccess
kerbMasterAccess.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the Kerberos master host. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Master', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbMasterAccessFailed.name: kerbMasterAccessFailed
kerbMasterAccessFailed.description: The number of times the system failed access to the Kerberos master host. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Master', and 'Unsuccessful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerAccess1.name: kerbServerAccess1
kerbServerAccess1.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the Kerberos primary server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerAccessFailed1.name: kerbServerAccessFailed1
kerbServerAccessFailed1.description: The number of times the system failed access to the Kerberos primary server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'Unsuccessful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerAccess2.name: kerbServerAccess2
kerbServerAccess2.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the Kerberos secondary server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbServerAccessFailed2.name: kerbServerAccessFailed2
kerbServerAccessFailed2.description: The number of times the system failed access to the Kerberos secondary server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'Unsuccessful:' in the SERVER KERBEROS display.

kerbPortTable.name: kerbPortTable
kerbPortTable.description: A list of Kerberos character port entries.

kerbPortEntry.name: kerbPortEntry
kerbPortEntry.description: Parameter values for a Kerberos port.

kerbPortIndex.name: kerbPortIndex
kerbPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port could relate to Kerberos. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

kerbPortStatus.name: kerbPortStatus
kerbPortStatus.description: A control indicating the level of Kerberos operation on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT KERBEROS and the value 'Kerberos' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

kerbServerPort.name: kerbServerPort
kerbServerPort.description: The UDP port number on the Kerberos server where Kerberos messages are sent.

psEntryNumber.name: psEntryNumber
psEntryNumber.description: The number of security entries in this system's port security table with psEntryStatus of 'valid'.

psEntryNumberLimit.name: psEntryNumberLimit
psEntryNumberLimit.description: The maximum number of security entries in this system's port security table.

psEntryInvalidIndex.name: psEntryInvalidIndex
psEntryInvalidIndex.description: A value of psEntryIndex for an entry that has psEntryStatus of 'invalid'. A management station may choose this value when adding a new entry. Collisions between independent management stations simultaneously using the same number are beyond the scope of this document.

psPortTable.name: psPortTable
psPortTable.description: A list of port security character port entries.

psPortEntry.name: psPortEntry
psPortEntry.description: Port security parameter values for a port.

psPortIndex.name: psPortIndex
psPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port for security purposes. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

psPortDefaultInboundAccess.name: psPortDefaultInboundAccess
psPortDefaultInboundAccess.description: The default access to the port for incoming TCP connections. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY DEFAULT INBOUND and the value labeled 'Inbound Default:' in the PORT INTERNET SECURITY display.

psPortDefaultOutboundAccess.name: psPortDefaultOutboundAccess
psPortDefaultOutboundAccess.description: The default access to the port for outgoing TCP connections. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY DEFAULT OUTBOUND and the value labeled 'Outbound Default:' in the PORT INTERNET SECURITY display.

psClrInternetSecurity.name: psClrInternetSecurity
psClrInternetSecurity.description: A control for if the internet security entries for this port will be cleared upon port logout. The default is disabled.

psTable.name: psTable
psTable.description: A list of port security entries.

psEntry.name: psEntry
psEntry.description: Port security parameter values for an entry for a port.

psEntryIndex.name: psEntryIndex
psEntryIndex.description: A small, numeric distinguisher for port security entries. When adding a new entry, the client should specify an unused value, such as psEntryInvalidIndex. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Entry' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

psEntryStatus.name: psEntryStatus
psEntryStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry, corresponding directly to the CLEAR INTERNET SECURITY command. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Setting this object to 'valid' has no effect. When creating a new instance, one must set psEntryAddress, psEntryMask, psEntryAccess, psEntryDirection and psEntryPortList for the new instance in the same physical set request. Furthermore, if one wishes to change an entry, one must first delete it and then add it with its new values.

psEntryAddress.name: psEntryAddress
psEntryAddress.description: The IP address to which the entry pertains. Corresponds directly to the PORT INTERNET SECURITY internet address and the value labeled 'Internet Address' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

psEntryMask.name: psEntryMask
psEntryMask.description: The mask applied to psEntryAddress when making a security check based on this entry. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY MASK and the value labeled 'Security Mask' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

psEntryAccess.name: psEntryAccess
psEntryAccess.description: The access to the port for TCP connections when making a security check based on this entry. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY ALLOW or DENY and the value labeled 'Access' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

psEntryDirection.name: psEntryDirection
psEntryDirection.description: The direction of TCP connections to which this entry applies. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY INBOUND or OUTBOUND and the value labeled 'Direction' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

psEntryPortMap.name: psEntryPortMap
psEntryPortMap.description: The list of character ports to which this entry applies. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each port, and enough octets for all the ports on the system. Port numbers are as defined for charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB. Corresponding bit numbers start with 1 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to PORT INTERNET SECURITY and the value labeled 'Ports' in the SERVER INTERNET SECURITY display.

xremoteServerName1.name: xremoteServerName1
xremoteServerName1.description: The Domain name of the first XREMOTE font server to try for downloading fonts. Corresponds directly to SERVER XREMOTE PRIMARY SERVER and the value labeled 'Xremote Primary Font Server:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteServerName2.name: xremoteServerName2
xremoteServerName2.description: The Domain name of the XREMOTE font server to try for downloading fonts and the primary font server does not respond. Corresponds directly to SERVER XREMOTE SECONDARY SERVER and the value labeled 'Xremote Secondary Font Server:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteServerAccess1.name: xremoteServerAccess1
xremoteServerAccess1.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the XREMOTE primary font server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteServerAccessFailed1.name: xremoteServerAccessFailed1
xremoteServerAccessFailed1.description: The number of times the system failed access to the XREMOTE primary font server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'Unsuccessful:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteServerAccess2.name: xremoteServerAccess2
xremoteServerAccess2.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the XREMOTE secondary font server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteServerAccessFailed2.name: xremoteServerAccessFailed2
xremoteServerAccessFailed2.description: The number of times the system failed access to the XREMOTE secondary font server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'Unsuccessful:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremoteSessions.name: xremoteSessions
xremoteSessions.description: The number of connected XREMOTE sessions. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Current Number of Xremote Sessions:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

xremotePortTable.name: xremotePortTable
xremotePortTable.description: A list of XREMOTE character port entries.

xremotePortEntry.name: xremotePortEntry
xremotePortEntry.description: XREMOTE parameter values for a port.

xremotePortIndex.name: xremotePortIndex
xremotePortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

xremotePortXremote.name: xremotePortXremote
xremotePortXremote.description: Control for use of XREMOTE on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT XREMOTE and the presence of the label 'Xremote' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

xremotePortXdmQuery.name: xremotePortXdmQuery
xremotePortXdmQuery.description: The type of query message issued by a port when searching for an X Display Manager (XDM). Corresponds directly to the PORT XDM QUERY and the 'XDM Query:' in the PORT ALTERNATE CHARACTERISTICS display

xremotePortXdmHost.name: xremotePortXdmHost
xremotePortXdmHost.description: The Domain name or Internet address of the X Display Manager (XDM) for a port. Corresponds directly to the PORT XDM HOST and the 'XDM Host:' in the PORT ALTERNATE CHARACTERISTICS display

xremoteServerClients.name: xremoteServerClients
xremoteServerClients.description: The number of active X clients. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Current Number of XClients:' in the SERVER XREMOTE display.

rotaryNumber.name: rotaryNumber
rotaryNumber.description: The number of entries in the Rotary table.

rotaryAddress.name: rotaryAddress
rotaryAddress.description: The internet address to be recognized as a rotary. Corresponds directly to the ip-address portion of SERVER INTERNET ROTARY and the value labeled 'Internet Address' in the SERVER INTERNET ROTARY display.

rotaryStatus.name: rotaryStatus
rotaryStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry, corresponding directly to the CLEAR SERVER INTERNET ROTARY command. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Setting the value to 'valid' in conjunction with a new rotaryAddress will add a new entry to the table. When adding a new entry, one should also specify a rotaryPortMap as the DEFVAL of 0..0 for rotaryPortMap is meaningless.

rotaryPortMap.name: rotaryPortMap
rotaryPortMap.description: The list of character ports that compose the rotary. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each port, and enough octets for all the ports on the system. Port numbers are as defined for charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB. Corresponding bit numbers start with 1 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to port-list portion of SERVER INTERNET ROTARY and the value labeled 'Ports' in the SERVER INTERNET ROTARY display.

egpStatus.name: egpStatus
egpStatus.description: Status of the EGP routing services indicating why it is not running.

egpNbrEntry.name: egpNbrEntry
egpNbrEntry.description: Information about this entity's relationship with a particular EGP neighbor.

egpNbrAddr.name: egpNbrAddr
egpNbrAddr.description: The IP address of this entry's EGP neighbor.

egpNbrIntervalDead.name: egpNbrIntervalDead
egpNbrIntervalDead.description: The interval upon entering the cease or idle state before automatically assuming a Start Event has occured. If a neighbor does not respond within 5 minutes, a Stop Event will automatically occur. The interval is in hundredths of seconds.

egpNbrStatus.name: egpNbrStatus
egpNbrStatus.description: The status of the entry for this neighbor. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

ospfAutoConfigure.name: ospfAutoConfigure
ospfAutoConfigure.description: Control whether OSPF will automatically configure itself.

ospfStatus.name: ospfStatus
ospfStatus.description: Status of the OSPF routing services indicating why it is not running.

ospfIfMtrcTable.name: ospfIfMtrcTable
ospfIfMtrcTable.description: The TOS metrics for a non-virtual interface identified by the interface index.

ospfIfMtrcEntry.name: ospfIfMtrcEntry
ospfIfMtrcEntry.description: A particular TOS metric for a non-virtual interface identified by the interface index.

ospfIfMtrcIpAddress.name: ospfIfMtrcIpAddress
ospfIfMtrcIpAddress.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfIfMtrcIpAddress.description: Same as ospfIfMetricIpAddress in OSPF MIB, the IP address of this OSPF interface.

ospfIfMtrcAddressLessIf.name: ospfIfMtrcAddressLessIf
ospfIfMtrcAddressLessIf.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfIfMtrcAddressLessIf.description: Same as ospfIfMetricAddressLessIf in OSPF MIB, for the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces. This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

ospfIfMtrcTos.name: ospfIfMtrcTos
ospfIfMtrcTos.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfIfMtrcTos.description: Same as ospfIfMetricTOS in OSPF MIB, the type of service metric being referenced.

ospfIfMtrcCostActual.name: ospfIfMtrcCostActual
ospfIfMtrcCostActual.description: The actual cost of the metric in case it was set to auto.

ospfXIfTable.name: ospfXIfTable
ospfXIfTable.description: The TOS metrics for a non-virtual interface identified by the interface index.

ospfXIfIpAddress.name: ospfXIfIpAddress
ospfXIfIpAddress.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfXIfIpAddress.description: Same as ospfIfIpAddress in OSPF MIB, the IP address of this OSPF interface.

ospfXIfAddressLessIf.name: ospfXIfAddressLessIf
ospfXIfAddressLessIf.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfXIfAddressLessIf.description: Same as ospfIfAddressLessIf in OSPF MIB, for the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces. This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

ospfXIfStatus.name: ospfXIfStatus
ospfXIfStatus.description: The status of the interface entry, including the entry in the standard OSPF MIB. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

ospfXAreaId.name: ospfXAreaId
ospfXAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, RFC 1253
ospfXAreaId.description: Same as ospfAreaId in OSPF MIB, the ID of the area.

ospfXAreaStatus.name: ospfXAreaStatus
ospfXAreaStatus.description: The status of the area entry, including the entry in the standard OSPF MIB. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

ipAdExtTable.name: ipAdExtTable
ipAdExtTable.description: Table of additional fields indexed by local IP address. An entry in this table is created or deleted when an entry in the ipAddrTable is created or deleted.

ipAdEntExtAddress.name: ipAdEntExtAddress
ipAdEntExtAddress.description: Same as ipAdEntAddr, a local address representing a network connection.

ipAdEntExtProxyArp.name: ipAdEntExtProxyArp
ipAdEntExtProxyArp.description: Controls whether proxy ARP is active for this local address.

ipAdEntExtRip.name: ipAdEntExtRip
ipAdEntExtRip.description: Controls whether RIP as a router discovery protocol is active for this local address.

ipRouterIfTable.name: ipRouterIfTable
ipRouterIfTable.description: Table of IP router values indexed by interface.

ipRouterIfIndex.name: ipRouterIfIndex
ipRouterIfIndex.description: The index of the interface; same as IfIndex.

ipRouterIfProtocolPriority.name: ipRouterIfProtocolPriority
ipRouterIfProtocolPriority.description: The priority at which all Internet routed packets will be placed on the WAN output queue.

ipRouterIfMTU.name: ipRouterIfMTU
ipRouterIfMTU.description: The size of the largest datagram that IP can transmit on this interface. The default value is actually hardware dependent.

ipRouterIfRDP.name: ipRouterIfRDP
ipRouterIfRDP.description: Control for whether the router side of the Router Discovery Protocol is running on this interface.

ipRouterIfArpPacketsIn.name: ipRouterIfArpPacketsIn
ipRouterIfArpPacketsIn.description: The number of ARP packets received on this interface.

ipRouterIfArpPacketsOut.name: ipRouterIfArpPacketsOut
ipRouterIfArpPacketsOut.description: The number of ARP packets sent on this interface.

ipRouterIfPacketsIn.name: ipRouterIfPacketsIn
ipRouterIfPacketsIn.description: The number of IP packets received on this interface.

ipRouterIfPacketsOut.name: ipRouterIfPacketsOut
ipRouterIfPacketsOut.description: The number of IP packets sent on this interface.

ipRouterIfForwardsIn.name: ipRouterIfForwardsIn
ipRouterIfForwardsIn.description: The number of IP packets received on this interface that were forwarded.

ipRouterIfForwardsOut.name: ipRouterIfForwardsOut
ipRouterIfForwardsOut.description: The number of IP packets sent on this interface that were forwarded.

ipTrafficSort.name: ipTrafficSort
ipTrafficSort.description: Setting to 'execute' causes the most recent traffic information to be sorted into the ipTrafficTable. The sorting precedence is: decreasing percentage, increasing destination address, increasing source address, and increasing interface number. Setting to 'ready' has no effect.

ipTrafficTable.name: ipTrafficTable
ipTrafficTable.description: A list of traffic entries, sorted in the order specified by ipTrafficSort.

ipTrafficPercent.name: ipTrafficPercent
ipTrafficPercent.description: The percentage of total traffic that this traffic entry represents, in tenths of a percent.

ipTrafficDstAddr.name: ipTrafficDstAddr
ipTrafficDstAddr.description: The destination IP address of the traffic entry.

ipTrafficSrcAddr.name: ipTrafficSrcAddr
ipTrafficSrcAddr.description: The source IP address of the traffic entry.

ipTrafficProtocol.name: ipTrafficProtocol
ipTrafficProtocol.description: The IP protocol type of the traffic entry.

ipTrafficDstPort.name: ipTrafficDstPort
ipTrafficDstPort.description: The destination TCP/UDP port of the traffic entry.

ipTrafficSrcPort.name: ipTrafficSrcPort
ipTrafficSrcPort.description: The source TCP/UDP port of the traffic entry.

ipTrafficIf.name: ipTrafficIf
ipTrafficIf.description: The inbound interface to which the traffic entry applies. This value is the same as IfIndex.

ipTrafficMonitoring.name: ipTrafficMonitoring
ipTrafficMonitoring.description: Control for whether the router side of the Router Discovery Protocol is running on this interface.

xIpNetToMediaTable.name: xIpNetToMediaTable
xIpNetToMediaTable.description: MRV In-Reach extensions to the IP Address Translation Table.

xIpNetToMediaCircuit.name: xIpNetToMediaCircuit
xIpNetToMediaCircuit.description: An additional identifier for the circuit (i.e. Frame Relay DLCI or X.25 VC) which the entry extends.

xIpNetToMediaReverseArp.name: xIpNetToMediaReverseArp
xIpNetToMediaReverseArp.description: Whether reverse ARP is supported on this entry.

udpBcstServerTable.name: udpBcstServerTable
udpBcstServerTable.description: Table of servers to whom UDP broadcast messages will be forwarded.

udpBcstServerStatus.name: udpBcstServerStatus
udpBcstServerStatus.description: The status of the server. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

udpBcstPortTable.name: udpBcstPortTable
udpBcstPortTable.description: Table of incoming UDP destination port numbers for which UDP broadcasts will be forwarded.

udpBcstPort.name: udpBcstPort
udpBcstPort.description: The incoming destination UDP port number.

udpBcstPortStatus.name: udpBcstPortStatus
udpBcstPortStatus.description: The status of broadcast forwarding for the port. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

udpBcstRouting.name: udpBcstRouting
udpBcstRouting.description: The indication of whether this entity forwards UDP broadcasts.

impEgpRuleEntry.name: impEgpRuleEntry
impEgpRuleEntry.description: An EGP import rule. Each rule is keyed by the Autonomous System of the EGP neighbor and the IP network of the route learned from the neighbor. The AS can be set to a wild card as can the IP network. When a route is learned from a neighbor, the most specific import rule is applied to the route. The route is either accepted or discarded and its metrics are applied according to the rule. An exact match on the AS and IP network is the most exact rule. An exact match on the AS and a wild card match on the IP network is the 2nd most exact rule. A wild card match on the AS and an exact match on the IP network is the 3rd most exact match. Finally, a total wild card match is the least exact rule.

impEgpRuleAs.name: impEgpRuleAs
impEgpRuleAs.description: The Autonomous System of the neighbor. The value 65535 is a wild card matching any AS number.

impEgpRuleNetwork.name: impEgpRuleNetwork
impEgpRuleNetwork.description: The IP network learned from the neighbor. The value 255.255.255.255 is a wild card matching any network.

impEgpRuleAction.name: impEgpRuleAction
impEgpRuleAction.description: Control whether the route is learned or discarded.

impEgpRulePreference.name: impEgpRulePreference
impEgpRulePreference.description: Preference to be stored with the route. The lower preference is preferred.

impEgpRuleType.name: impEgpRuleType
impEgpRuleType.description: Type to be stored with the route. The type is based on the OSPF external type and used to help compare metrics. Type 1 is preferred over type 2.

impEgpRuleMetricAction.name: impEgpRuleMetricAction
impEgpRuleMetricAction.description: How to apply the impEgpRuleMetric field to the metric learned with the route before storing it in the routing table.

impEgpRuleMetric.name: impEgpRuleMetric
impEgpRuleMetric.description: Metric value to be applied to the metric learned learned with the route before storing it in the routing table.

impEgpRuleStatus.name: impEgpRuleStatus
impEgpRuleStatus.description: The status of the rule. Set to 'invalid' to remove the rule. If the all wild card rule is removed, it is automatically readded with default values.

impOspfRuleEntry.name: impOspfRuleEntry
impOspfRuleEntry.description: An OSPF import rule. Each rule is keyed by the IP network of the route and the AS from which it was learned. The Ip network and the AS can both be set to a wild card. When an OSPF route is added to the routing table, the most specific import rule is applied to set the preference of the route. An exact match on the Ip network and on the AS is the most exact rule. An exact match on the IP network and a wild card match on the AS is the 2nd most exact rule. A wild card match on both the on the AS and IP network is the next and least exact rule.

impOspfRuleNetwork.name: impOspfRuleNetwork
impOspfRuleNetwork.description: The IP network of the route. The value 255.255.255.255 is a wild card matching any network.

impOspfRulePreference.name: impOspfRulePreference
impOspfRulePreference.description: Preference to be stored with the route. The lower preference is preferred.

impOspfRuleStatus.name: impOspfRuleStatus
impOspfRuleStatus.description: The status of the rule. Set to 'invalid' to remove the rule. If the all wild card rule is removed, it is automatically readded with default values.

impRipRuleEntry.name: impRipRuleEntry
impRipRuleEntry.description: A RIP import rule. Each rule is keyed by the interface and the IP network of the route learned from the neighbor. The route is either accepted or discarded and its metrics are applied according to the rule. An exact match on the IP network is the rule that will be applied. If an exact match does not exist, the rule with the wild card IP network is used.

impRipRuleFromIf.name: impRipRuleFromIf
impRipRuleFromIf.description: The interface index of the interface where the rule applies, same as ifIndex.

impRipRuleNetwork.name: impRipRuleNetwork
impRipRuleNetwork.description: The IP network learned from the neighbor. The value 255.255.255.255 is a wild card matching any network.

impRipRuleAction.name: impRipRuleAction
impRipRuleAction.description: Control whether the route is learned or discarded.

impRipRulePreference.name: impRipRulePreference
impRipRulePreference.description: Preference to be stored with the route. The lower preference are preferred.

impRipRuleType.name: impRipRuleType
impRipRuleType.description: Type to be stored with the route. The type is based on the OSPF external type and used to help compare metrics. Type 1 is preferred over type 2.

impRipRuleMetricAction.name: impRipRuleMetricAction
impRipRuleMetricAction.description: How to apply the impRipRuleMetric field to the metric learned with the route before storing it in the routing table.

impRipRuleMetric.name: impRipRuleMetric
impRipRuleMetric.description: Metric value to be applied to the metric learned learned with the route before storing it in the routing table.

impRipRuleStatus.name: impRipRuleStatus
impRipRuleStatus.description: The status of the rule. Set to 'invalid' to remove the rule. If the all wild card rule is removed, it is automatically readded with default values.

impIsisRuleEntry.name: impIsisRuleEntry

expOspfToIsisRuleTable.name: expOspfToIsisRuleTable
expOspfToIsisRuleTable.description: The Ospf to Isis export table.

expOspfToIsisRuleEntry.name: expOspfToIsisRuleEntry
expOspfToIsisRuleEntry.description: An Ospf to Isis export rule. Each rule is keyed by the Autonomous System of the Ospf neighbor, the IP network of the Ospf route in the routing table, and the Autonomous System from which the route was learned. The IP network can be set to a wild card as can the the from AS. The route is either accepted to be advertised to the neighbor or discarded from being advertised, and its metric is applied according to the rule. The best match is as follows: IP Network From AS Best Match Rank exact exact 1st exact wild card 2nd wild card exact 3rd wild card wild card 4th .

expOspfToIsisRuleNetwork.name: expOspfToIsisRuleNetwork
expOspfToIsisRuleNetwork.description: The IP network of the route in the route table. The value 255.255.255.255 is a wild card matching any network.

expOspfToIsisRuleFromAs.name: expOspfToIsisRuleFromAs
expOspfToIsisRuleFromAs.description: The Autonomous System of the route in the route table. The value 65535 is a wild card matching any AS number, and the value 65534 is for routes within the local AS.

expOspfToIsisRuleAction.name: expOspfToIsisRuleAction
expOspfToIsisRuleAction.description: Control whether the route is advertised or not.

expOspfToIsisRuleMetricType.name: expOspfToIsisRuleMetricType
expOspfToIsisRuleMetricType.description: Whether to advertise the metric as Internal or External.
