ipIfFilterIndex.name: ipIfFilterIndex
ipIfFilterIndex.description: The interface index with which this entry is associated. This value is the same as IfIndex.

ipIfFilterDstAddr.name: ipIfFilterDstAddr
ipIfFilterDstAddr.description: The destination IP address to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilterDstMask.name: ipIfFilterDstMask
ipIfFilterDstMask.description: The destination IP mask to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilterSrcAddr.name: ipIfFilterSrcAddr
ipIfFilterSrcAddr.description: The source IP address to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilterSrcMask.name: ipIfFilterSrcMask
ipIfFilterSrcMask.description: The source IP mask to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilterProtocol.name: ipIfFilterProtocol
ipIfFilterProtocol.description: The protocol to use in the filter match. The value 256 indicates any protocol.

ipIfFilterDstPort.name: ipIfFilterDstPort
ipIfFilterDstPort.description: The destination port to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets. The value 65536 indicates any destination port.

ipIfFilterSrcPort.name: ipIfFilterSrcPort
ipIfFilterSrcPort.description: The source port to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets. The value 65536 indicates any source port.

ipIfFilterAction.name: ipIfFilterAction
ipIfFilterAction.description: Control whether the packet for which this filter is the best match should be forwarded or discarded.

ipIfFilterStatus.name: ipIfFilterStatus
ipIfFilterStatus.description: The status of the filter entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

ipFilterState.name: ipFilterState
ipFilterState.description: The indication of whether this system does IP filtering.

ipIfFilter2Index.name: ipIfFilter2Index
ipIfFilter2Index.description: The interface index with which this entry is associated. This value is the same as IfIndex.

ipIfFilter2DstAddr.name: ipIfFilter2DstAddr
ipIfFilter2DstAddr.description: The destination IP address to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilter2DstMask.name: ipIfFilter2DstMask
ipIfFilter2DstMask.description: The destination IP mask to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilter2SrcAddr.name: ipIfFilter2SrcAddr
ipIfFilter2SrcAddr.description: The source IP address to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilter2SrcMask.name: ipIfFilter2SrcMask
ipIfFilter2SrcMask.description: The source IP mask to use in the filter match.

ipIfFilter2Protocol.name: ipIfFilter2Protocol
ipIfFilter2Protocol.description: The protocol to use in the filter match. The value 256 indicates any protocol.

ipIfFilter2DstPortStart.name: ipIfFilter2DstPortStart
ipIfFilter2DstPortStart.description: The starting destination port in a range of destination ports to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets.

ipIfFilter2SrcPortStart.name: ipIfFilter2SrcPortStart
ipIfFilter2SrcPortStart.description: The starting source port in a range of source ports to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets.

ipIfFilter2Action.name: ipIfFilter2Action
ipIfFilter2Action.description: Control whether the packet for which this filter is the best match should be forwarded or discarded.

ipIfFilter2Status.name: ipIfFilter2Status
ipIfFilter2Status.description: The status of the filter entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry.

ipIfFilter2DstPortEnd.name: ipIfFilter2DstPortEnd
ipIfFilter2DstPortEnd.description: The ending destination port in a range of destination ports to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets. This filed must also be greater or equal to the ipIfFilter2DstPortStart field.

ipIfFilter2SrcPortEnd.name: ipIfFilter2SrcPortEnd
ipIfFilter2SrcPortEnd.description: The starting source port in a range of source ports to use in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP and UDP protocol packets. This filed must also be greater or equal to the ipIfFilter2SrcPortStart field.

ipIfFilter2TcpSyn.name: ipIfFilter2TcpSyn
ipIfFilter2TcpSyn.description: The value of the TCP SYN and ACK bit to ues in the filter match. This field only applies to TCP packets. On indicates that the SYN bit is on and the ACK bit is off. Off is any other combination.

ipIfFilter2ProtocolPriority.name: ipIfFilter2ProtocolPriority
ipIfFilter2ProtocolPriority.description: Control the priority at which the packet for which this filter is the best match should be placed on the WAN output queue. None indicates that the sending interfaces protocol priority should be used.

ripState.name: ripState
ripState.description: The indication of whether this system participates in RIP.

ripStatus.name: ripStatus
ripStatus.description: The status of the RIP software.

ripNetNet.name: ripNetNet
ripNetNet.description: The IP Network to which this entry applies.

ripNetState.name: ripNetState
ripNetState.description: This value controls the RIP protocol on this network.

ripNetRipsIn.name: ripNetRipsIn
ripNetRipsIn.description: The number of RIP packets received from routers on this IP network.

ripNetRipsOut.name: ripNetRipsOut
ripNetRipsOut.description: The number of RIP packets sent to routers on this IP network.

ripNetAlgorithm.name: ripNetAlgorithm
ripNetAlgorithm.description: This value controls the RIP algorithm on this network.

lpdQueueTable.name: lpdQueueTable
lpdQueueTable.description: A list of lpd queues on the server.

lpdQueueEntry.name: lpdQueueEntry
lpdQueueEntry.description: Lpd parameter values plus counters for an individual lpd queue.

lpdQueueStatus.name: lpdQueueStatus
lpdQueueStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry, corresponding directly to the CLEAR/PURGE SERVER LPD QUEUE command. Setting the value to 'valid' validates (creates) the entry, corresonding directly to the DEF/SET SERVER LPD QUEUE and lpd create commands.

lpdQueueName.name: lpdQueueName
lpdQueueName.description: Name of the LPD queue, case sensitive.

lpdQueuePorts.name: lpdQueuePorts
lpdQueuePorts.description: List of ports assigned to the queue. An lpd queue can be associated with more than 1 port. This object corresponds to the port-list in the DEF/SET SERVER LPD QUEUE and lpc/create commands. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each port, and enough octets for all the ports on the system. Port numbers are as defined for charPortIndex in the Character MIB [11]. Corresponding bit numbers start with 1 as the high-order bit of the first octet.

lpdQueueEnabled.name: lpdQueueEnabled
lpdQueueEnabled.description: Flag indicates if the queue is enabled. A 'disabled' queue will reject print requests from remote systems. A 'enabled' queue accepts requests for printing.

lpdQueueLfConversion.name: lpdQueueLfConversion
lpdQueueLfConversion.description: Flag indicates if the queue is converting linefeeds to linefeeds, carriagereturns. 'lfcr' does the converion, 'lf' does not.

lpdQueueTotalJobs.name: lpdQueueTotalJobs
lpdQueueTotalJobs.description: The total number of jobs on the queue. This number should be equal to the number of active and waiting jobs. (lpdQueueActive + lpdQueueWaiting)

lpdQueueActiveJobs.name: lpdQueueActiveJobs
lpdQueueActiveJobs.description: The number of active jobs on the queue. An active job is a job that has been assigned a port is in the process of receiving data from a remote host and sending it out the port.

lpdQueueWaitingJobs.name: lpdQueueWaitingJobs
lpdQueueWaitingJobs.description: The number of waiting jobs on the queue. A waiting job is a job that needs a port to send its data to. This implies that the ports associated with this queue are busy.

lpdQueueProcessedJobs.name: lpdQueueProcessedJobs
lpdQueueProcessedJobs.description: The total number of jobs processed by this queue since server boot.

lpdQueueFormFeed.name: lpdQueueFormFeed
lpdQueueFormFeed.description: A control to determine how we will send out a formfeed when printing a lpd job. formfeedafter: Send after job, formfeedbefore: Send before job, formfeednone: Send no formfeed.

lpdQueueBypass.name: lpdQueueBypass
lpdQueueBypass.description: Control for a queue to bypass a LPD port which has output inhibited via flow control. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Bypass' in the SERVER LPD QUEUE display.

lpdJobStatus.name: lpdJobStatus
lpdJobStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting this object to 'invalid' will remove the job from the queue. Setting this object ot 'valid' has no effect since the only way to create an lpd job is with the lpd protocol.

lpdJobNumber.name: lpdJobNumber
lpdJobNumber.description: The queue relative job number for this lpd job. Job numbers are assigned as jobs are accepted onto the queue. Job numbers are reset to 1 when they reach a value greater than 1000 and the queue goes empty.

lpdJobAssignedPort.name: lpdJobAssignedPort
lpdJobAssignedPort.description: The number of the port assigned to the lpd job.

lpdJobFileSize.name: lpdJobFileSize
lpdJobFileSize.description: The size of the file being sent from the remote system.

lpdJobHostName.name: lpdJobHostName
lpdJobHostName.description: The name of the host sending the job.

lpdJobFileName.name: lpdJobFileName
lpdJobFileName.description: The name of the file being sent.

lpdJobState.name: lpdJobState
lpdJobState.description: The current state of the lpd job. A typical job transistions through the following states: initialize->waiting->assigned->printingdata-> printingcontrol->completed.

securIDServerName0.name: securIDServerName0
securIDServerName0.description: The Domain name of the first SecurID server to try when the system verifies a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID SERVER0 and the value labeled 'SecurID Server0:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerName1.name: securIDServerName1
securIDServerName1.description: The Domain name of the second SecurID server to try when the system verifies a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID SERVER1 and the value labeled 'SecurID Server1:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerName2.name: securIDServerName2
securIDServerName2.description: The Domain name of the third SecurID server to try when the system verifies a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID SERVER2 and the value labeled 'SecurID Server2:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerName3.name: securIDServerName3
securIDServerName3.description: The Domain name of the fourth SecurID server to try when the system verifies a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID SERVER3 and the value labeled 'SecurID Server3:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerName4.name: securIDServerName4
securIDServerName4.description: The Domain name of the fifth SecurID server to try when the system verifies a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID SERVER4 and the value labeled 'SecurID Server4:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDMaxRetries.name: securIDMaxRetries
securIDMaxRetries.description: The maximum number of times the server will try any single SecurID server to validate a PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID ACMMAXRETRIES and the value labeled 'SecurID ACMMAXRETRIES:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDBaseTimeout.name: securIDBaseTimeout
securIDBaseTimeout.description: The initial timeout value to be used between prompts for a SecurID PASSCODE. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID ACMBASETIMEOUT and the value labeled 'SecurID ACMBASETIMEOUT:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDPort.name: securIDPort
securIDPort.description: The UDP port number to be used when communicating with the SecurID servers. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID ACM_PORT and the value labeled 'SecurID ACM_PORT:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDQueryLimit.name: securIDQueryLimit
securIDQueryLimit.description: The maximum number of times a user will be queried for a SecurID PASSCODE before being logged out. Corresponds directly to SERVER SECURID QUERY LIMIT and the value labeled 'SecurID Query Limit:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDEncryptionMode.name: securIDEncryptionMode
securIDEncryptionMode.description: The type of encryption to use in SecurID validation. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Encryption Mode' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDInsecureLogins.name: securIDInsecureLogins
securIDInsecureLogins.description: The number of user logins on ports for which SecurID user verification is not enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Logins without SecurID:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDSecureLogins.name: securIDSecureLogins
securIDSecureLogins.description: The number of successful user logins on ports for which SecurID user verification is enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Successful Logins:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDSecureLoginsFailed.name: securIDSecureLoginsFailed
securIDSecureLoginsFailed.description: The number of verification failures due to incorrect PASSCODE for attempted user logins on ports for which SecurID user verification is enabled. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Unsuccessful Logins:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccess0.name: securIDServerAccess0
securIDServerAccess0.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the SecurID server0. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server0', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccessFailed0.name: securIDServerAccessFailed0
securIDServerAccessFailed0.description: The number of times the system unsuccessfully accessed the SecurID server0. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server0', and 'UnSuccessful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccess1.name: securIDServerAccess1
securIDServerAccess1.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the SecurID server1. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccessFailed1.name: securIDServerAccessFailed1
securIDServerAccessFailed1.description: The number of times the system unsuccessfully accessed the SecurID server1. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server1', and 'UnSuccessful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccess2.name: securIDServerAccess2
securIDServerAccess2.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the SecurID server2. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccessFailed2.name: securIDServerAccessFailed2
securIDServerAccessFailed2.description: The number of times the system unsuccessfully accessed the SecurID server2. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server2', and 'UnSuccessful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccess3.name: securIDServerAccess3
securIDServerAccess3.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the SecurID server3. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server3', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccessFailed3.name: securIDServerAccessFailed3
securIDServerAccessFailed3.description: The number of times the system unsuccessfully accessed the SecurID server3. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server3', and 'UnSuccessful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccess4.name: securIDServerAccess4
securIDServerAccess4.description: The number of times the system successfully accessed the SecurID server4. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server4', and 'Successful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDServerAccessFailed4.name: securIDServerAccessFailed4
securIDServerAccessFailed4.description: The number of times the system unsuccessfully accessed the SecurID server4. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Attempts to access:', 'Server4', and 'UnSuccessful:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDErrorPortIndex.name: securIDErrorPortIndex
securIDErrorPortIndex.description: The index of the most recent port on which a SecurID access violation occurred. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Last Unsuccessful Login:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDError.name: securIDError
securIDError.description: The error number of the most recent SecurID-related error. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Reason:' in the SERVER SECURID display. See MRV In-Reach documentation for a complete list of error numbers and their meaning.

securIDErrorUsername.name: securIDErrorUsername
securIDErrorUsername.description: The username associated with the most recent SecurID-related error. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Username:' in the SERVER SECURID display.

securIDPortTable.name: securIDPortTable
securIDPortTable.description: A list of SecurID character port entries.

securIDPortEntry.name: securIDPortEntry
securIDPortEntry.description: Parameter values for a SecurID port.

securIDPortIndex.name: securIDPortIndex
securIDPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port could relate to SecurID. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

securIDPortStatus.name: securIDPortStatus
securIDPortStatus.description: A control indicating the level of SecurID operation on the port. Corresponds directly to PORT SECURID and the value 'SecurID' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshPortTable.name: sshPortTable
sshPortTable.description: A list of SSH port entries

sshPortEntry.name: sshPortEntry
sshPortEntry.description: Parameter values for an SSH port.

sshPortIndex.name: sshPortIndex
sshPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an SSH port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the proposed standard Internet Character MIB.

sshPortIncomingTcpPort.name: sshPortIncomingTcpPort
sshPortIncomingTcpPort.description: Specifies the TCP port number used to identify the port when a SSH connection request arrives at the server. The default for a physical port is 2022 + 100 * port's physical port number. The default is 22 for virtual ports. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Remote Port:' in the PORT SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshPortNewlineFiltering.name: sshPortNewlineFiltering
sshPortNewlineFiltering.description: Translation to apply to newline sequences (CR/NULL or CR/LF) received from the network during a SSH session, before sending the newline to the character port. The value indicates which input sequence is converted to which output sequence and sent to the character port, with 'none' meaning no translation. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Newline Filtering:' in the PORT SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshPortNewline.name: sshPortNewline
sshPortNewline.description: Translation to apply to newline (carriage return) received from the character port during an SSH session, before sending the newline to the remote partner. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Newline:' in the PORT SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshPortTransmitBufferedTime.name: sshPortTransmitBufferedTime
sshPortTransmitBufferedTime.description: Number of milliseconds to wait before transmitting data received from a character port during an interactive SSH session. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Transmit Buffered Time:' in the PORT SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshPortRemoteProtocol.name: sshPortRemoteProtocol
sshPortRemoteProtocol.description: Indicates which remote protocols will be accepted at this port. Corresponds indirectly to the presence of 'Telnet' or 'SSH' under the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the PORT SSH CHARACTERISTICS display. If both protocols are accepted at the port, the choice of protocol is determined by which features are enabled on the server with SSH taking precedence over Telnet.

sshPortBreakSequence.name: sshPortBreakSequence
sshPortBreakSequence.description: A sequence of characters, which together define the break function. If this string is received from the SSH connection from across the network, the port will send a hardware break out of the serial port. The first character must be a carriage return ('\r'), and no more carriage returns may appear in the sequence. The second character must not be a NULL, or a line-feed ('\n'). Send a NULL to remove the break sequence. If the sequence exists, it must have two to four characters.

sshCipherMask.name: sshCipherMask
sshCipherMask.description: This is a list of the encryption methods supported. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each cipher type. Corresponding bit numbers start with 0 as the low-order bit of the second octet. The following bit positions are defined: none(0), des(2), tripleDes(3), and blowfish(6). Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'SSH Cipher Enabled:' in the SERVER SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshAuthenticationTimeout.name: sshAuthenticationTimeout
sshAuthenticationTimeout.description: The timeout in minutes before disconnecting if no successful authentication of SSH parties has been made. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Authentication Timeout:' in the SERVER SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshHostKeyLength.name: sshHostKeyLength
sshHostKeyLength.description: The bit length of the SSH host encryption key. When modified, the desired change does not occur until the next system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Host Key Length:' in the SERVER SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshHostKeyGenerate.name: sshHostKeyGenerate
sshHostKeyGenerate.description: For a set-request with a value of generate or update, a new host key will be generated in the background. When modified with generate, the desired change does not occur until the next system initialization whereas when modified with update the change goes into effect upon completion of the new key. In response to a get-request or a get-next-request the agent will respond ready except when a host key is being created in which case the agent responds generate.

sshServerKeyLength.name: sshServerKeyLength
sshServerKeyLength.description: The bit length of the SSH server encryption key. The difference between the server and host key lengths should be greater than 128 bits. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Server Key Length:' in the SERVER SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshServerKeyTtl.name: sshServerKeyTtl
sshServerKeyTtl.description: The time in minutes that the server key remains valid. After this time the server key is automatically re-generated. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Server Key Timeout:' in the SERVER SSH CHARACTERISTICS display.

sshServerMaxBufferSize.name: sshServerMaxBufferSize
sshServerMaxBufferSize.description: The size of the four buffers used by SSH for input and output. These buffers are used for data coming from the console, going to the network, coming from the network and going to the console.

ipxInternalNetwork.name: ipxInternalNetwork
ipxInternalNetwork.description: The IPX Internal Network to use on the the IPX Router.

ipxIfTable.name: ipxIfTable
ipxIfTable.description: A list of IPX interface entries.

ipxIfIndex.name: ipxIfIndex
ipxIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an IPX interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ipxIfState.name: ipxIfState
ipxIfState.description: Control for IPX routing services for this interface.

ipxIfNetwork.name: ipxIfNetwork
ipxIfNetwork.description: The IPX network number of the network to which this interface is attached.

ipxIfFrameStyle.name: ipxIfFrameStyle
ipxIfFrameStyle.description: Control for the CSMA/CD frame style to use on this interface.

ipxIfFramesIn.name: ipxIfFramesIn
ipxIfFramesIn.description: The number of IPX frames received on this interface.

ipxIfFramesOut.name: ipxIfFramesOut
ipxIfFramesOut.description: The number of IPX frames sent on this interface.

ipxIfErrors.name: ipxIfErrors
ipxIfErrors.description: The number of IPX errors seen on this interface.

ipxIfTransitDelay.name: ipxIfTransitDelay
ipxIfTransitDelay.description: The number of 55 millisecond ticks it takes for a packet to travel from one destination to another on the interface. A value of 0 means that the system will calculate this value based on the measured speed of the interface.

ipxIfTransitDelayActual.name: ipxIfTransitDelayActual
ipxIfTransitDelayActual.description: The number of 55 millisecond ticks it takes for a packet to travel from one destination to another on the interface.

ipxIfProtocolPriority.name: ipxIfProtocolPriority
ipxIfProtocolPriority.description: This value defines the priority at which all Internet Routed packets will be placed on the WAN output queue.

ipxIfWatchdogSpoof.name: ipxIfWatchdogSpoof
ipxIfWatchdogSpoof.description: Control for whether or not this router responds to IPX watchog requests on this interface.

ipxIfStatusNetwork.name: ipxIfStatusNetwork
ipxIfStatusNetwork.description: The IPX network number that is actually in use on the attached interface. This value may have been learned via listening to the attached network.

ipxNetbiosHopLimit.name: ipxNetbiosHopLimit
ipxNetbiosHopLimit.description: Maximum number of hops that an IPX Netbios packet may make.

ipxNetbiosIfTable.name: ipxNetbiosIfTable
ipxNetbiosIfTable.description: A list of IPX interface entries.

ipxNetbiosIfIndex.name: ipxNetbiosIfIndex
ipxNetbiosIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an IPX interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ipxIfNetbiosForwarding.name: ipxIfNetbiosForwarding
ipxIfNetbiosForwarding.description: Control whether Netbios packet will be forwarded in or out on this interface.

ipxIfNetbiosIn.name: ipxIfNetbiosIn
ipxIfNetbiosIn.description: The number of IPX Netbios frames received on this interface.

ipxIfNetbiosOut.name: ipxIfNetbiosOut
ipxIfNetbiosOut.description: The number of IPX Netbios frames sent on this interface.

ipxRipIfTable.name: ipxRipIfTable
ipxRipIfTable.description: A list of IPX interface entries.

ipxRipIfIndex.name: ipxRipIfIndex
ipxRipIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an IPX interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ipxIfRipBcst.name: ipxIfRipBcst
ipxIfRipBcst.description: Control whether RIP packets will be broadcasted out this interface.

ipxIfRipBcstDiscardTimeout.name: ipxIfRipBcstDiscardTimeout
ipxIfRipBcstDiscardTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait before discarding information learned from a RIP broadcast.

ipxIfRipBcstTimer.name: ipxIfRipBcstTimer
ipxIfRipBcstTimer.description: The number of seconds to wait between sending out RIP broadcasts.

ipxIfRipIn.name: ipxIfRipIn
ipxIfRipIn.description: The number of RIP broadcasts received on this interface.

ipxIfRipOut.name: ipxIfRipOut
ipxIfRipOut.description: The number of RIP broadcasts sent on this interface.

ipxIfRipAgedOut.name: ipxIfRipAgedOut
ipxIfRipAgedOut.description: The number of entries timed out and discarded on this interface.

ipxRipNetwork.name: ipxRipNetwork
ipxRipNetwork.description: An IPX network number to which this router knows a path.

ipxRipRouter.name: ipxRipRouter
ipxRipRouter.description: The Ethernet address of an IPX router on this network.

ipxRipInterface.name: ipxRipInterface
ipxRipInterface.description: The interface to reach the router. A value of ifIndex.

ipxRipHops.name: ipxRipHops
ipxRipHops.description: The number of hops to reach the router.

ipxRipTransTime.name: ipxRipTransTime
ipxRipTransTime.description: The number of 55 millisecond ticks it takes for a packet to travel to the router.

ipxRipAge.name: ipxRipAge
ipxRipAge.description: The age of the RIP entry in seconds.

ipxRipRtTable.name: ipxRipRtTable
ipxRipRtTable.description: A list of RIP Routing entries.

ipxRipRtNetwork.name: ipxRipRtNetwork
ipxRipRtNetwork.description: An IPX network number to which this router knows a path.

ipxRipRtRouter.name: ipxRipRtRouter
ipxRipRtRouter.description: The Ethernet address of an IPX router on this network.

ipxRipRtInterface.name: ipxRipRtInterface
ipxRipRtInterface.description: The interface to reach the router. A value of ifIndex.

ipxRipRtHops.name: ipxRipRtHops
ipxRipRtHops.description: The number of hops to reach the router.

ipxRipRtTransTime.name: ipxRipRtTransTime
ipxRipRtTransTime.description: The number of 55 millisecond ticks it takes for a packet to travel to the router.

ipxRipRtOrigin.name: ipxRipRtOrigin
ipxRipRtOrigin.description: The source of the RIP entry, either Learned via RIP or Static.

ipxRipRtRowStatus.name: ipxRipRtRowStatus
ipxRipRtRowStatus.description: Create or Delete RIP routing table entries.

ipxSapIfTable.name: ipxSapIfTable
ipxSapIfTable.description: A list of IPX interface entries.

ipxSapIfIndex.name: ipxSapIfIndex
ipxSapIfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an IPX interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ipxIfSapBcst.name: ipxIfSapBcst
ipxIfSapBcst.description: Control whether SAP packets will be broadcasted out this interface.

ipxIfSapBcstDiscardTimeout.name: ipxIfSapBcstDiscardTimeout
ipxIfSapBcstDiscardTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait before discarding information learned from a SAP broadcast.

ipxIfSapBcstTimer.name: ipxIfSapBcstTimer
ipxIfSapBcstTimer.description: The number of seconds to wait between sending out SAP broadcasts.

ipxIfSapIn.name: ipxIfSapIn
ipxIfSapIn.description: The number SAP broadcasts received on this interface.

ipxIfSapOut.name: ipxIfSapOut
ipxIfSapOut.description: The number SAP broadcasts sent on this interface.

ipxIfSapAgedOut.name: ipxIfSapAgedOut
ipxIfSapAgedOut.description: The number entries for this interface discarded due to aging timeout.

ipxSapName.name: ipxSapName
ipxSapName.description: The name of the service, null filled.

ipxSapNetwork.name: ipxSapNetwork
ipxSapNetwork.description: The IPX network number on which the service's host resides.

ipxSapHost.name: ipxSapHost
ipxSapHost.description: The Ethernet address of the IPX host of the service.

ipxSapSocket.name: ipxSapSocket
ipxSapSocket.description: The socket number of the service on the host.

ipxSapInterface.name: ipxSapInterface
ipxSapInterface.description: The interface of the router in the direction of the service. A value of ifIndex.

ipxSapType.name: ipxSapType
ipxSapType.description: The type of the service. The enumeration is an incomplete set of all possible values.

ipxSapAge.name: ipxSapAge
ipxSapAge.description: The age of the Sap entry in seconds.

ipxSapSvNetwork.name: ipxSapSvNetwork
ipxSapSvNetwork.description: The IPX network number on which the service's host resides.

ipxSapSvHost.name: ipxSapSvHost
ipxSapSvHost.description: The Ethernet address of the IPX host of the service.

ipxSapSvSocket.name: ipxSapSvSocket
ipxSapSvSocket.description: The socket number of the service on the host.

ipxSapSvInterface.name: ipxSapSvInterface
ipxSapSvInterface.description: The interface of the router in the direction of the service. A value of ifIndex.

ipxSapSvOrigin.name: ipxSapSvOrigin
ipxSapSvOrigin.description: The source of the RIP entry, either Learned via RIP or Static.

ipxSapSvType.name: ipxSapSvType
ipxSapSvType.description: The type of the service. The enumeration is an incomplete set of all possible values.

ipxSapSvHops.name: ipxSapSvHops
ipxSapSvHops.description: The number of hops to the Service.

ipxSapSvRowStatus.name: ipxSapSvRowStatus
ipxSapSvRowStatus.description: Create or Delete SAP Service table entries.

ipxSapSvAge.name: ipxSapSvAge
ipxSapSvAge.description: The age of the Sap entry in seconds.

ipxIfFilterTable.name: ipxIfFilterTable
ipxIfFilterTable.description: A list of IPX interface Source and Destination address Filter entries.

ipxIfFilterEntry.name: ipxIfFilterEntry
ipxIfFilterEntry.description: IPX Source and Destination interface Filters.

ipxIfFilterIndex.name: ipxIfFilterIndex
ipxIfFilterIndex.description: The interface to which this IPX Address filter applies. A value of ifIndex.

ipxIfFilterDestNetwork.name: ipxIfFilterDestNetwork
ipxIfFilterDestNetwork.description: The destination IPX network to be filtered.

ipxIfFilterDestNode.name: ipxIfFilterDestNode
ipxIfFilterDestNode.description: The destination IPX node to be filtered.

ipxIfFilterSourceNetwork.name: ipxIfFilterSourceNetwork
ipxIfFilterSourceNetwork.description: The destination IPX network to be filtered.

ipxIfFilterSourceNode.name: ipxIfFilterSourceNode
ipxIfFilterSourceNode.description: The destination IPX node to be filtered.

ipxIfFilterPacketType.name: ipxIfFilterPacketType
ipxIfFilterPacketType.description: The IPX packet type to be filtered.

ipxIfFilterAction.name: ipxIfFilterAction
ipxIfFilterAction.description: The IPX filter action to be taken, either Forward or Discard.

ipxIfFilterRowStatus.name: ipxIfFilterRowStatus
ipxIfFilterRowStatus.description: The IPX Filter create or delete function.

ipxIfFilterStatusDestNetworkAll.name: ipxIfFilterStatusDestNetworkAll
ipxIfFilterStatusDestNetworkAll.description: The IPX Filter flag meaning ALL destination networks.

ipxIfFilterStatusDestNodeAll.name: ipxIfFilterStatusDestNodeAll
ipxIfFilterStatusDestNodeAll.description: The IPX Filter flag meaning ALL destination nodes.

ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNetworkAll.name: ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNetworkAll
ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNetworkAll.description: The IPX Filter flag meaning ALL source networks.

ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNodeAll.name: ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNodeAll
ipxIfFilterStatusSourceNodeAll.description: The IPX Filter flag meaning ALL source nodes.

ipxIfFilterStatusPacketTypeAll.name: ipxIfFilterStatusPacketTypeAll
ipxIfFilterStatusPacketTypeAll.description: The IPX Filter flag meaning ALL packet types.

ipxIfRipFilterTable.name: ipxIfRipFilterTable
ipxIfRipFilterTable.description: A list of IPX interface RIP Filter entries.

ipxIfRipFilterNetwork.name: ipxIfRipFilterNetwork
ipxIfRipFilterNetwork.description: The IPX RIP network to be filtered.

ipxIfRipFilterType.name: ipxIfRipFilterType
ipxIfRipFilterType.description: The IPX RIP filter type, either IMPORT or EXPORT.

ipxIfRipFilterAction.name: ipxIfRipFilterAction
ipxIfRipFilterAction.description: The IPX RIP filter action to be taken, either ALLOW or DENY.

ipxIfRipFilterRowStatus.name: ipxIfRipFilterRowStatus
ipxIfRipFilterRowStatus.description: The IPX RIP Filter create or delete function.

ipxIfRipFilterNetworkAll.name: ipxIfRipFilterNetworkAll
ipxIfRipFilterNetworkAll.description: The IPX RIP Filter flag meaning filter ALL networks.

ipxIfRipFilterHost.name: ipxIfRipFilterHost
ipxIfRipFilterHost.description: The RIP Filter IPX Host Address from which RIP will ALLOW/DENY IMPORT of routes.

ipxIfSapFilterTable.name: ipxIfSapFilterTable
ipxIfSapFilterTable.description: A list of IPX interface SAP Filter entries.

ipxIfSapFilterNetwork.name: ipxIfSapFilterNetwork
ipxIfSapFilterNetwork.description: The IPX SAP network to be filtered.

ipxIfSapFilterType.name: ipxIfSapFilterType
ipxIfSapFilterType.description: The IPX SAP filter type, either IMPORT or EXPORT.

ipxIfSapFilterServiceType.name: ipxIfSapFilterServiceType
ipxIfSapFilterServiceType.description: The IPX SAP service type to which this filter applies.

ipxIfSapFilterAction.name: ipxIfSapFilterAction
ipxIfSapFilterAction.description: The IPX SAP filter action to be taken, either ALLOW or DENY.

ipxIfSapFilterRowStatus.name: ipxIfSapFilterRowStatus
ipxIfSapFilterRowStatus.description: The IPX SAP Filter create or delete function.

ipxIfSapFilterNetworkAll.name: ipxIfSapFilterNetworkAll
ipxIfSapFilterNetworkAll.description: The IPX SAP Filter flag meaning filter ALL networks.

ipxIfSapFilterServiceTypeAll.name: ipxIfSapFilterServiceTypeAll
ipxIfSapFilterServiceTypeAll.description: The IPX SAP Filter flag meaning filter ALL service types.

ipxIfSapFilterName.name: ipxIfSapFilterName
ipxIfSapFilterName.description: The name of the service to be filtered.

ipxIfSapFilterHost.name: ipxIfSapFilterHost
ipxIfSapFilterHost.description: The IPX Host address from which SAP will ALLOW/DENY IMPORT of services .

ipxPrinterPortTable.name: ipxPrinterPortTable
ipxPrinterPortTable.description: A list of IPX printer character port entries.

ipxPrinterPortEntry.name: ipxPrinterPortEntry
ipxPrinterPortEntry.description: IPX printer parameter values for a character port.

ipxPrinterPortIndex.name: ipxPrinterPortIndex
ipxPrinterPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Proposed Standard Internet Character MIB.

ipxPrinterPortStatus.name: ipxPrinterPortStatus
ipxPrinterPortStatus.description: Status of this entry. Setting the value to 'invalid' invalidates the entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table.

ipxPrinterPortServer.name: ipxPrinterPortServer
ipxPrinterPortServer.description: The name of an active print server on the network.

ipxPrinterPortPrinter.name: ipxPrinterPortPrinter
ipxPrinterPortPrinter.description: An available remote printer on ixpPrinterPortServer.

ipxTimeout.name: ipxTimeout
ipxTimeout.description: A control to set the the time at which a print job from a print server will be timed out and the port freed.

ipxPrinterEthernet.name: ipxPrinterEthernet
ipxPrinterEthernet.description: Control for use of Ethernet-style message framing, with the IPX protocol type. Mutually exclusive with ipxPrinterMac, ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap, and ipxPrinterMac802_2.

ipxPrinterMac.name: ipxPrinterMac
ipxPrinterMac.description: Control for use of MAC-only message framing, with no protocol type. Mutually exclusive with ipxPrinterEthernet, ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap, and ipxPrinterMac802_2.

ipxPrinterMac802_2.name: ipxPrinterMac802_2
ipxPrinterMac802_2.description: Control for use of MAC message framing with 802.2 framing. Mutually exclusive with ipxPrinterEthernet, ipxPrinterMac, and ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap.

ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap.name: ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap
ipxPrinterMac802_2_Snap.description: Control for use of MAC-only message framing with 802 Snap framing. Mutually exclusive with ipxPrinterEthernet, ipxPrinterMac, and ipxPrinterMac802_2.

latAnnounceServices.name: latAnnounceServices
latAnnounceServices.description: Control for automatic, periodic announcement of local services to the network. Corresponds directly to SERVER ANNOUNCEMENTS and the presence of the label 'Announcements' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latCircuitTimer.name: latCircuitTimer
latCircuitTimer.description: Number of milleseconds to collect port input data before sending it to the host. Corresponds directly to SERVER CIRCUIT TIMER and the value labeled 'Circuit Timer:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latIdentificationLengthLimit.name: latIdentificationLengthLimit
latIdentificationLengthLimit.description: Maximum number of characters to store in the instances of latVisibleServiceIdentification. Corresponds directly to SERVER IDENTIFICATION SIZE and the value labeled 'Identification Size:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latKeepaliveTimer.name: latKeepaliveTimer
latKeepaliveTimer.description: Number of seconds of inactivity before sending a null message to the host. Corresponds directly to SERVER KEEPALIVE TIMER and the value labeled 'Keepalive Timer:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latMulticastTimer.name: latMulticastTimer
latMulticastTimer.description: Number of seconds between transmission of local service announcements. Corresponds directly to SERVER MULTICAST TIMER and the value labeled 'Multicast Timer:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latNodeLimit.name: latNodeLimit
latNodeLimit.description: Maximum number of service nodes to keep in the node table. Corresponds directly to SERVER NODE LIMIT and the value labeled 'Node Limit:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latNumber.name: latNumber
latNumber.description: An arbitrary number assigned and used for administrative purposes. Corresponds directly to SERVER NUMBER and the value labeled 'Number:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latRetransmitLimit.name: latRetransmitLimit
latRetransmitLimit.description: Maximum number of times to retransmit an unacknowledged message. Corresponds directly to SERVER RETRANSMIT LIMIT and the value labeled 'Retransmit Limit:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latLocalServiceGroups.name: latLocalServiceGroups
latLocalServiceGroups.description: The list of group numbers allowed to use local services, where a group number is in the range 0-255. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each group. Corresponding bit numbers start with 0 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to SERVER SERVICE GROUPS and the value labeled 'Service Groups:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latGroupPurge.name: latGroupPurge
latGroupPurge.description: Control for automatic deletion of all node table entries when latServiceGroups or latPortCurrentGroups is changed. Corresponds directly to SERVER PURGE GROUP and the presence of the label 'Purge Group' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latNodePurge.name: latNodePurge
latNodePurge.description: Control for automatic deletion of all node table entries with status 'reachable' when the number of entries exceeds latNodeLimit. Corresponds directly to SERVER PURGE NODE and the presence of the label 'Purge Node' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latNodesRejected.name: latNodesRejected
latNodesRejected.description: Number of nodes not added to the node table because there was no room. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Discarded Nodes:' in the SERVER STATUS display.

latInMessages.name: latInMessages
latInMessages.description: Number of LAT messages received. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Received:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latOutMessages.name: latOutMessages
latOutMessages.description: Number of LAT messages sent. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Transmitted:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInSessionsAccepted.name: latInSessionsAccepted
latInSessionsAccepted.description: Number of incoming LAT session connection attempts accepted. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Solicitations Accepted:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInSessionsRejected.name: latInSessionsRejected
latInSessionsRejected.description: Number of incoming LAT session connection attempts rejected. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Solicitations Rejected:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latAddressChange.name: latAddressChange
latAddressChange.description: Number of times a service announcement contained a node name already in the visible service table but with a different address. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Multiple Node Addresses:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInDuplicates.name: latInDuplicates
latInDuplicates.description: Number of duplicate LAT messages received. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Duplicates Received:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latOutRetransmits.name: latOutRetransmits
latOutRetransmits.description: Number of LAT messages retransmitted due to no acknowledgement. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Re-transmitted:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInBadMessages.name: latInBadMessages
latInBadMessages.description: Number of LAT messages received with invalid format. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Illegal Messages Rcv'd:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInBadSlots.name: latInBadSlots
latInBadSlots.description: Number of LAT messages received with invalid slot format. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Illegal Slots Rcv'd:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latInBadMulticasts.name: latInBadMulticasts
latInBadMulticasts.description: Number of multicast LAT messages received with invalid format. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Illegal Multicasts Rcv'd:' in the SERVER COUNTERS display.

latPortTable.name: latPortTable
latPortTable.description: A list of LAT character port entries.

latPortEntry.name: latPortEntry
latPortEntry.description: LAT parameter values for a port.

latPortIndex.name: latPortIndex
latPortIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a port. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by charPortIndex in the Character MIB [11].

latPortAuthorizedGroups.name: latPortAuthorizedGroups
latPortAuthorizedGroups.description: The list of group numbers to which the port is allowed to set access, where a group number is in the range 0-255. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each group. Corresponding bit numbers start with 0 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to PORT AUTHORIZED GROUPS and the value labeled 'Authorized Groups:' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

latPortAutoPrompt.name: latPortAutoPrompt
latPortAutoPrompt.description: Control for automatic stimulation of a host prompt upon forming a new session. Corresponds directly to PORT AUTOPROMPT and the presence of the label 'Autoprompt' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

latPortCurrentGroups.name: latPortCurrentGroups
latPortCurrentGroups.description: The list of group numbers to which the port currently has set access, where a group number is in the range 0-255. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each group. Corresponding bit numbers start with 0 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to PORT GROUPS and the value labeled 'Groups:' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

latPortRemoteModification.name: latPortRemoteModification
latPortRemoteModification.description: Control to allow the remote system to modify certain physical port characteristics. Corresponds directly to PORT REMOTE MODIFICATION and the presence of the label 'Remote Modification' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the PORT CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServiceTable.name: latOfferedServiceTable
latOfferedServiceTable.description: A list of offered service entries.

latOfferedServiceEntry.name: latOfferedServiceEntry
latOfferedServiceEntry.description: Parameter values for an offered service entry.

latOfferedServiceName.name: latOfferedServiceName
latOfferedServiceName.description: The name of an offered service. Corresponds directly to the name in a SERVICE command and the value labeled 'Service:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServiceStatus.name: latOfferedServiceStatus
latOfferedServiceStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the CLEAR SERVICE command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

latOfferedServiceAllowConnections.name: latOfferedServiceAllowConnections
latOfferedServiceAllowConnections.description: Control for allowing incoming connections to the service. Corresponds directly to SERVICE CONNECTIONS and the presence of the label 'Connections' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServiceIdentification.name: latOfferedServiceIdentification
latOfferedServiceIdentification.description: Text to identify a service. Corresponds directly to SERVICE IDENTIFICATION and the value labeled 'Identification:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServicePassword.name: latOfferedServicePassword
latOfferedServicePassword.description: The password a user must supply to use the service. Corresponds directly to SERVICE PASSWORD and the presence of the label 'Password' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display. When setting this value, the management system must supply eight octets, filling with zeros from the first octet. That is, the value '1ab42' would be expressed as '0.0.0.0.0.1.ab.42'. Setting the value to zero disables the password check. When returning this value, the agent always returns a zero length OCTET STRING.

latOfferedServicePortMap.name: latOfferedServicePortMap
latOfferedServicePortMap.description: The list of character ports offer the service. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each port, and enough octets for all the ports on the system. Port numbers are as defined for charPortIndex in the Character MIB [11]. Corresponding bit numbers start with 1 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to port-list portion of SERVICE PORTS and the value labeled 'Ports:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServiceQueuing.name: latOfferedServiceQueuing
latOfferedServiceQueuing.description: Control for allowing queuing of incoming connections to the service when the service is busy. Corresponds directly to SERVICE QUEUE and the presence of the label 'Queuing' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVICE CHARACTERISTICS display.

latOfferedServiceEnvironmentalManager.name: latOfferedServiceEnvironmentalManager
latOfferedServiceEnvironmentalManager.description: Control indicating whether Environmental Management services are offered.

latVisibleServiceTable.name: latVisibleServiceTable
latVisibleServiceTable.description: A list of visible service entries.

latVisibleServiceEntry.name: latVisibleServiceEntry
latVisibleServiceEntry.description: Parameter values for a visible service entry.

latVisibleServiceName.name: latVisibleServiceName
latVisibleServiceName.description: The name of a visible service. Corresponds directly to the name in a SERVICE command and the value labeled 'Service Name' in the SERVICE SUMMARY display.

latVisibleServiceStatus.name: latVisibleServiceStatus
latVisibleServiceStatus.description: Status of communication with the service. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Status' in the SERVICE SUMMARY display.

latVisibleServiceNode.name: latVisibleServiceNode
latVisibleServiceNode.description: Name of a node offering the service. Corresponds directly to the value labeled Node Name in the SERVICE STATUS display.

latVisibleServiceConnectedSessions.name: latVisibleServiceConnectedSessions
latVisibleServiceConnectedSessions.description: Number of connected sessions to the service. Corresponds directly to the number with the value 'Connected', labeled 'Status' in the SERVICE SUMMARY display.

latVisibleServiceIdentification.name: latVisibleServiceIdentification
latVisibleServiceIdentification.description: Text to identify a service. The length is subject to limitation by latIdentificationLengthLimit. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Identification:' in the SERVICE SUMMARY display.

latVisibleServiceRating.name: latVisibleServiceRating
latVisibleServiceRating.description: Relative capacity of the service to accept additional sessions. Corresponds directly to value labeled Rating in the SERVICE STATUS display.

latNodeEntry.name: latNodeEntry
latNodeEntry.description: Parameter values for a node entry.

latNodeName.name: latNodeName
latNodeName.description: The name of a node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Node:' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeStatus.name: latNodeStatus
latNodeStatus.description: Status of communication with the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Status' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeConnectedSessions.name: latNodeConnectedSessions
latNodeConnectedSessions.description: Number of connected sessions to the node. Corresponds directly to the number with the value 'Connected', labeled 'Status' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeAddress.name: latNodeAddress
latNodeAddress.description: Ethernet address of the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Address:' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeDataLinkFrame.name: latNodeDataLinkFrame
latNodeDataLinkFrame.description: Maximum Ethernet frame used by the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Data Link Frame Size:' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeIdentification.name: latNodeIdentification
latNodeIdentification.description: Text that identifies the node. The size is subject to limitation by latIdentificationLengtLimit. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Identification' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeGroups.name: latNodeGroups
latNodeGroups.description: The list of group numbers to which the node belongs, where a group number is in the range 0-255. The OCTET STRING contains a bitmap, with one bit for each group. Corresponding bit numbers start with 0 as the high-order bit of the first octet. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Node Groups:' in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeServiceNumber.name: latNodeServiceNumber
latNodeServiceNumber.description: Number of entries for the node in the node service table. Corresponds indirectly to the list of services in the NODE STATUS display.

latNodeZero.name: latNodeZero
latNodeZero.description: Control to zero counters kept for the node. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes all the system's counters to be zeroed. Corresponds to the ZERO NODE command.

latNodeZeroTime.name: latNodeZeroTime
latNodeZeroTime.description: The number of hundredths of a second since the most recent zeroing of the counters kept for the node, such as through execution of sysZeroAll or latNodeZero. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Seconds Since Zeroed:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInMessages.name: latNodeInMessages
latNodeInMessages.description: The number of LAT messages received from the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeOutMessages.name: latNodeOutMessages
latNodeOutMessages.description: The number of LAT messages sent to the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Transmitted:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInSlots.name: latNodeInSlots
latNodeInSlots.description: The number of LAT slots received from the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Slots Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeOutSlots.name: latNodeOutSlots
latNodeOutSlots.description: The number of LAT slots sent to the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Slots Transmitted:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInBytes.name: latNodeInBytes
latNodeInBytes.description: The total number of bytes received from the node, including Ethernet overhead. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Bytes Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeOutBytes.name: latNodeOutBytes
latNodeOutBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent to the node, including Ethernet overhead. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Bytes Transmitted:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeAddressChange.name: latNodeAddressChange
latNodeAddressChange.description: The number of times a LAT message multicast by the node had a different Ethernet address from the previous time. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Multiple Node Addresses:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInDuplicates.name: latNodeInDuplicates
latNodeInDuplicates.description: The number of duplicate LAT message received from the node. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Duplicates Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeOutRetransmits.name: latNodeOutRetransmits
latNodeOutRetransmits.description: The number of LAT message retransmitted to the node due to lack of acknowledgement. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Messages Re-transmitted:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInBadMessages.name: latNodeInBadMessages
latNodeInBadMessages.description: The number of LAT message received from the node with invalid format. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Illegal Messages Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInBadSlots.name: latNodeInBadSlots
latNodeInBadSlots.description: The number of LAT slots received from the node with invalid format. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Illegal Slots Received:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInSessionsAccepted.name: latNodeInSessionsAccepted
latNodeInSessionsAccepted.description: The number of LAT session connection attempts received from the node and accepted. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Solicitations Accepted:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latNodeInSessionsRejected.name: latNodeInSessionsRejected
latNodeInSessionsRejected.description: The number of LAT session connection attempts received from the node and rejected. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Solicitations Rejected:' in the NODE COUNTERS display.

latSolicits.name: latSolicits
latSolicits.description: Control for multicast solicitation of LAT services. Corresponds directly to SERVER LAT SOLICITAIONS and the presence of the label 'LAT SOLICITATIONS' following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

latImmediateAck.name: latImmediateAck
latImmediateAck.description: Control for LAT to provide an immediate ACK, and not to wait for the timer to expire. Corresponds directly to SERVER LAT IMMEDIATE ACK and the presence of the label 'LAT Immediate Ack following the label 'Enabled Characteristics:' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramClientLoaderName.name: paramClientLoaderName
paramClientLoaderName.description: The name of the system that most recently provided this system's stored parameters. Corresponds directly to the name value labeled 'Loaded From:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientLoaderAddressType.name: paramClientLoaderAddressType
paramClientLoaderAddressType.description: The type of network address contained in paramClientLoaderAddress. 'unknown' means no address has been defined. 'other' means no other type value applies. 'local' means there is no address and parameters were loaded from local storage. 'ip' is an Internet IP address. 'ethernet' is an 802.3 MAC address. Corresponds indirectly to the address value labeled 'Loaded From:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientLoaderAddress.name: paramClientLoaderAddress
paramClientLoaderAddress.description: The network address of the system that most recently provided this system's stored parameters. Corresponds directly to the address value labeled 'Loaded From:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientParameterVersion.name: paramClientParameterVersion
paramClientParameterVersion.description: The version number of the parameters as stored in this system's local memory. Corresponds directly to SERVER PARAMETER VERSION and the value labeled 'Last Update Version:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientUpdateTime.name: paramClientUpdateTime
paramClientUpdateTime.description: This system's local date and time when it last attempted to store parameters with a parameter server. Corresponds directly to the values labeled 'Last Update Date:' and 'Last Update Time:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientServerCheck.name: paramClientServerCheck
paramClientServerCheck.description: Control over whether or not this system is allowed to check for additional parameter servers. 'enabled' allows checking. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER CHECK and the presence of PARAMETER POLLING under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramClientCheckInterval.name: paramClientCheckInterval
paramClientCheckInterval.description: The number of minutes between checks for additional parameter servers. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER CHECK TIMER and the value labeled 'Check Timer:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientCheckNow.name: paramClientCheckNow
paramClientCheckNow.description: Control to cause this system to immediately check for additional parameter servers. The agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes a check to be started. Corresponds to the CHECK PARAMETER SERVER command.

paramClientServerLimit.name: paramClientServerLimit
paramClientServerLimit.description: The maximum number of parameter servers this system is allowed to remember at the same time. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER LIMIT and the value labeled 'Parameter Server Limit:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientRetransmitInterval.name: paramClientRetransmitInterval
paramClientRetransmitInterval.description: The number of minutes between this system's attempts to store new parameters with a server that has not acknowledged previous attempts. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER RETRANSMIT TIMER and the value labeled 'Retransmit Timer: in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientRetransmitLimit.name: paramClientRetransmitLimit
paramClientRetransmitLimit.description: The maximum number of attempts by this system to store new parameters with a server that has not acknowledged previous attempts. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER RETRANSMIT LIMIT and the value labeled 'Retransmit Limit:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientState.name: paramClientState
paramClientState.description: This system's state with regard to update attempts. The value meanings are: other none of the following idle no update in progress internal internal state of no meaning to manager hold holding to keep from updating too often retry waiting to retry after failure Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Storage State:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientProtocolErrors.name: paramClientProtocolErrors
paramClientProtocolErrors.description: The number of invalid parameter service protocol messages received by this system. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Bad Parameter Messages:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientServerRejects.name: paramClientServerRejects
paramClientServerRejects.description: The number of parameter servers this system rejected due to exceeding paramClientServerLimit. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Rejected Servers:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientServerNumber.name: paramClientServerNumber
paramClientServerNumber.description: The number of parameter servers known to this system, indicating the number of entries in serverTable. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Parameter Servers:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerTable.name: paramServerTable
paramServerTable.description: A list of parameter server entries. The number of entries is given by the value of paramClientServerNumber.

paramServerEntry.name: paramServerEntry
paramServerEntry.description: Status and parameter values for a parameter server.

paramServerName.name: paramServerName
paramServerName.description: The server's name, unique within this system. Always 16 characters, null padded on the end. Corresponds directly to the name used to create the entry and the value labeled 'Name' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerEntryStatus.name: paramServerEntryStatus
paramServerEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the CLEAR/PURGE PARAMETER SERVER command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

paramServerAddressType.name: paramServerAddressType
paramServerAddressType.description: The type of network address contained in paramServerAddress. 'unknown' means no address has been defined. 'other' means no other type value applies. 'local' means there is no address and parameters were loaded from local storage. 'ip' is an Internet IP address. 'ethernet' is an 802.3 MAC address. Corresponds indirectly to the value labeled 'Address' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerAddress.name: paramServerAddress
paramServerAddress.description: The server's network address. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Address' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerStoredVersion.name: paramServerStoredVersion
paramServerStoredVersion.description: Parameter version number currently stored at the server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Version' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerStoredTime.name: paramServerStoredTime
paramServerStoredTime.description: The server's date and time when it stored the parameters of version paramServerStoredVersion. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Date' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramServerStoredStatus.name: paramServerStoredStatus
paramServerStoredStatus.description: Status of this system's parameters with respect to the server. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Status' in the PARAMETER SERVER display. The value meanings are: ahead server version newer than system's behind server version older than system's current up to date failed system no longer attempting update failing system trying to update but failing query attempting to determine version noMemCard no memory card in card drive unknown version not known

paramServerStoredFailure.name: paramServerStoredFailure
paramServerStoredFailure.description: When paramServerStoredStatus is 'failed' or 'failing', the reason for the most recent failure. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Reason' in the PARAMETER SERVER display. The value meanings are: other none of the following none no failure protocolOut invalid protocol message to server open file open error at server read file read error at server write file write error at server resource resource lack at server (e.g. disk) protocolIn invalid protocol message from server response no response from server close file close error at server delete file delete error at server rename file rename error at server fileData bad parameter data stored at server

paramClientPath.name: paramClientPath
paramClientPath.description: The directory path to the parameter file on all servers. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVER PATH and the value labeled 'Path:' in the PARAMETER SERVER display.

paramClientChassisStorageState.name: paramClientChassisStorageState
paramClientChassisStorageState.description: The status of the current attempt to update parameters in local chassis storage. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Chassis Configuration:'.

paramClientTftpBroadcast.name: paramClientTftpBroadcast
paramClientTftpBroadcast.description: Control over whether or not this system is allowed to send out a TFTP read broadcast after sending a BOOTP broadcast during the Parameter Check Function. 'enabled' allows TFTP broadcast. Corresponds directly to the presence of PARAMETER TFTP BROADCAST under the label 'Enabled Characteristics' in the SERVER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramClientWriteNow.name: paramClientWriteNow
paramClientWriteNow.description: Control to start saving parameters immediately in response to an execute. Corresponds directly to the WRITE PARAMETERS command. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value.

xPppConfigTable.name: xPppConfigTable
xPppConfigTable.description: A table containing PPP specific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppConfigEntry.name: xPppConfigEntry
xPppConfigEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP.

xPppConfigOpen.name: xPppConfigOpen
xPppConfigOpen.description: Determines if PPP is configured on this port.

xPppConfigActive.name: xPppConfigActive
xPppConfigActive.description: Determines if LCP will actively open or wait passively.

xPppConfigDefaults.name: xPppConfigDefaults
xPppConfigDefaults.description: Revert to factory default PPP parameters. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' sets PPP parameters to factory defaults.

xPppConfigRestartTimer.name: xPppConfigRestartTimer
xPppConfigRestartTimer.description: The number of seconds waited before retransmitting during option negotiation.

xPppConfigConfLimit.name: xPppConfigConfLimit
xPppConfigConfLimit.description: Maximum number of times a configuration request will be sent to the peer without receiving a response.

xPppConfigFailLimit.name: xPppConfigFailLimit
xPppConfigFailLimit.description: Maximum number of times a peer's proposed option will be NAKed before REJECTing the option.

xPppConfigPacketLogging.name: xPppConfigPacketLogging
xPppConfigPacketLogging.description: Determines the level of packet logging to accounting on this port.

xPppConfigKATimer.name: xPppConfigKATimer
xPppConfigKATimer.description: Determines the number of seconds between transmission of LCP Echo Keepalive packets.

xPppConfigKATimeout.name: xPppConfigKATimeout
xPppConfigKATimeout.description: Determines the number of seconds to wait to hear LCP Echo Replies to our Echo Request Keepalive packets before giving up and shutting down the link.

xPppStatusTable.name: xPppStatusTable
xPppStatusTable.description: A table containing basic PPP status info.

xPppStatusEntry.name: xPppStatusEntry
xPppStatusEntry.description: Status information about a particular PPP.

xPppStatusState.name: xPppStatusState
xPppStatusState.description: Displays whether PPP is enabled or disabled on this port.

xPppLinkOpen.name: xPppLinkOpen
xPppLinkOpen.description: Displays open status of the link.

xPppHdlcRxTotalPkts.name: xPppHdlcRxTotalPkts
xPppHdlcRxTotalPkts.description: Total of all packets received on PPP link.

xPppHdlcTxTotalPkts.name: xPppHdlcTxTotalPkts
xPppHdlcTxTotalPkts.description: Total of all packets transmitted on PPP link.

xPppHdlcRxFrameErrs.name: xPppHdlcRxFrameErrs
xPppHdlcRxFrameErrs.description: Number of framing errors received on PPP link.

xPppHdlcRxNoBuffer.name: xPppHdlcRxNoBuffer
xPppHdlcRxNoBuffer.description: Number of times a buffer was not available to receive packet into.

xPppHdlcTxNoBuffer.name: xPppHdlcTxNoBuffer
xPppHdlcTxNoBuffer.description: Number of times a buffer was not available to transmit a packet from.

xPppHdlcRxBadFcs.name: xPppHdlcRxBadFcs
xPppHdlcRxBadFcs.description: Number of packets received with a bad checksum.

xPppHdlcVJDiscards.name: xPppHdlcVJDiscards
xPppHdlcVJDiscards.description: Number of packets received that failed VJ decompression.

xPppLcpConfigTable.name: xPppLcpConfigTable
xPppLcpConfigTable.description: A table containing PPP LCP specific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppLcpConfigEntry.name: xPppLcpConfigEntry
xPppLcpConfigEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP LCP session.

xPppLcpConfigAuth.name: xPppLcpConfigAuth
xPppLcpConfigAuth.description: Authentication protocol used for authenticating peers.

xPppLcpConfigChapAuth.name: xPppLcpConfigChapAuth
xPppLcpConfigChapAuth.description: Authentication CHAP protocol used for authenticating peers.

xPppLcpStatusTable.name: xPppLcpStatusTable
xPppLcpStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP LCP status info.

xPppLcpStatusEntry.name: xPppLcpStatusEntry
xPppLcpStatusEntry.description: Status information about a particular PPP LCP session.

xPppLcpStatusRxAuth.name: xPppLcpStatusRxAuth
xPppLcpStatusRxAuth.description: The authentication protocol currently in use from the peer to us.

xPppLcpStatusTxAuth.name: xPppLcpStatusTxAuth
xPppLcpStatusTxAuth.description: The authentication protocol currently in use from us to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxConReq.name: xPppLcpStatusRxConReq
xPppLcpStatusRxConReq.description: The count of LCP Configure Requests received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxConReq.name: xPppLcpStatusTxConReq
xPppLcpStatusTxConReq.description: The count of LCP Configure Requests transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxConNak.name: xPppLcpStatusRxConNak
xPppLcpStatusRxConNak.description: The count of LCP Configure Naks received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxConNak.name: xPppLcpStatusTxConNak
xPppLcpStatusTxConNak.description: The count of LCP Configure Naks transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxConAck.name: xPppLcpStatusRxConAck
xPppLcpStatusRxConAck.description: The count of LCP Configure Acks received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxConAck.name: xPppLcpStatusTxConAck
xPppLcpStatusTxConAck.description: The count of LCP Configure Acks transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxConRej.name: xPppLcpStatusRxConRej
xPppLcpStatusRxConRej.description: The count of LCP Configure Rejects received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxConRej.name: xPppLcpStatusTxConRej
xPppLcpStatusTxConRej.description: The count of LCP Configure Rejects transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxTrmReq.name: xPppLcpStatusRxTrmReq
xPppLcpStatusRxTrmReq.description: The count of LCP Terminate Requests received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxTrmReq.name: xPppLcpStatusTxTrmReq
xPppLcpStatusTxTrmReq.description: The count of LCP Terminate Requests transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxTrmAck.name: xPppLcpStatusRxTrmAck
xPppLcpStatusRxTrmAck.description: The count of LCP Terminate Acks received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxTrmAck.name: xPppLcpStatusTxTrmAck
xPppLcpStatusTxTrmAck.description: The count of LCP Terminate Acks transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxEcoReq.name: xPppLcpStatusRxEcoReq
xPppLcpStatusRxEcoReq.description: The count of LCP Echo Requests received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxEcoReq.name: xPppLcpStatusTxEcoReq
xPppLcpStatusTxEcoReq.description: The count of LCP Echo Requests transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxEcoRep.name: xPppLcpStatusRxEcoRep
xPppLcpStatusRxEcoRep.description: The count of LCP Echo Reply received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxEcoRep.name: xPppLcpStatusTxEcoRep
xPppLcpStatusTxEcoRep.description: The count of LCP Echo Reply transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxCodRej.name: xPppLcpStatusRxCodRej
xPppLcpStatusRxCodRej.description: The count of LCP Code Rejects received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxCodRej.name: xPppLcpStatusTxCodRej
xPppLcpStatusTxCodRej.description: The count of LCP Code Rejects transmitted to the peer.

xPppLcpStatusRxProRej.name: xPppLcpStatusRxProRej
xPppLcpStatusRxProRej.description: The count of LCP Protocol Rejects received from the peer.

xPppLcpStatusTxProRej.name: xPppLcpStatusTxProRej
xPppLcpStatusTxProRej.description: The count of LCP Protocol Rejects transmitted to the peer.

xPppIpcpConfigTable.name: xPppIpcpConfigTable
xPppIpcpConfigTable.description: A table containing PPP IPCPspecific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppIpcpConfigEntry.name: xPppIpcpConfigEntry
xPppIpcpConfigEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP IPCP session.

xPppIpcpConfigLocalAddress.name: xPppIpcpConfigLocalAddress
xPppIpcpConfigLocalAddress.description: IP Address of the local PPP interface.

xPppIpcpConfigRemoteAddress.name: xPppIpcpConfigRemoteAddress
xPppIpcpConfigRemoteAddress.description: IP Address of the peer PPP interface.

xPppIpcpConfigVJCompSlots.name: xPppIpcpConfigVJCompSlots
xPppIpcpConfigVJCompSlots.description: Number of slots to be used by VJ compression.

xPppIpcpConfigRangeStart.name: xPppIpcpConfigRangeStart
xPppIpcpConfigRangeStart.description: Start of acceptable address range in which the negotiated remote IP address must fall.

xPppIpcpConfigRangeEnd.name: xPppIpcpConfigRangeEnd
xPppIpcpConfigRangeEnd.description: End of acceptable address range in which the negotiated remote IP address must fall.

xPppIpcpConfigState.name: xPppIpcpConfigState
xPppIpcpConfigState.description: Controls whether IPCP is allowed to run on this port.

xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeStart.name: xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeStart
xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeStart.description: Start of acceptable address range in which the negotiated local IP address must fall.

xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeEnd.name: xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeEnd
xPppIpcpConfigLocalRangeEnd.description: End of acceptable address range in which the negotiated local IP address must fall.

xPppIpcpConfigPppIpMask.name: xPppIpcpConfigPppIpMask
xPppIpcpConfigPppIpMask.description: The subnet mask to use for a PPP operation on the port. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'IP Mask:' in the PPP PORT IP CHARACTERISTICS display.

xPppIpcpAsyncConfigTable.name: xPppIpcpAsyncConfigTable
xPppIpcpAsyncConfigTable.description: A table containing PPP specific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppIpcpAsyncConfigEntry.name: xPppIpcpAsyncConfigEntry
xPppIpcpAsyncConfigEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP Asynchronous LCP.

xPppIpcpAsyncConfigBrdcast.name: xPppIpcpAsyncConfigBrdcast
xPppIpcpAsyncConfigBrdcast.description: Determines whether to forward an IP Broadcast or not.

xPppIpcpStatusTable.name: xPppIpcpStatusTable
xPppIpcpStatusTable.description: A table containing basic PPP IPCP status info.

xPppIpcpStatusEntry.name: xPppIpcpStatusEntry
xPppIpcpStatusEntry.description: Status information about a particular PPP IPCP session.

xPppIpcpStatusLocalAddress.name: xPppIpcpStatusLocalAddress
xPppIpcpStatusLocalAddress.description: The IP Address currently being used by the local IPCP.

xPppIpcpTxPkts.name: xPppIpcpTxPkts

xPppIpcpRxTrmAck.name: xPppIpcpRxTrmAck
xPppIpcpRxTrmAck.description: The count of IPCP Terminate Acks received from the peer.

xPppIpcpTxTrmAck.name: xPppIpcpTxTrmAck

xPppAuthChapChallengeTimer.name: xPppAuthChapChallengeTimer
xPppAuthChapChallengeTimer.description: Length of time in minutes between CHAP reauthentication challenges. A value of zero disables the timer.

xPppAuthPapConfigState.name: xPppAuthPapConfigState
xPppAuthPapConfigState.description: Controls the type of Pap authentication required for this port, and whether it is combined with another authentication mechanism such as Radius.

xPppAuthChapConfigState.name: xPppAuthChapConfigState
xPppAuthChapConfigState.description: Controls the type of Chap authentication required for this port, and whether it is combined with another authentication mechanism such as Radius.

xPppAuthStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP specific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppIpxcpConfigRemoteNode.name: xPppIpxcpConfigRemoteNode
xPppIpxcpConfigRemoteNode.description: The IPX Node address which can be offered to the peer if it does not know a Node number but requires one.

xPppIpxcpStatusTable.name: xPppIpxcpStatusTable
xPppIpxcpStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP specific variables for this PPP implementation.

xPppIpxcpStatusEntry.name: xPppIpxcpStatusEntry

xPppIpxcpCipxOutCompression.name: xPppIpxcpCipxOutCompression
xPppIpxcpCipxOutCompression.description: The current state of CIPX compression outbound.

xPppIpxcpCipxInSlots.name: xPppIpxcpCipxInSlots
xPppIpxcpCipxInSlots.description: The current number of CIPX compression inbound slots.

xPppIpxcpCipxOutSlots.name: xPppIpxcpCipxOutSlots
xPppIpxcpCipxOutSlots.description: The current number of CIPX compression outbound slots.

xPppIpxcpStatusRemoteNode.name: xPppIpxcpStatusRemoteNode
xPppIpxcpStatusRemoteNode.description: The IPX Node address currently being used by the Remote IPX peer.

xPppIpxcpCountersTable.description: A table containing basic PPP IPXCP status info.

xPppIpxcpCountersEntry.description: Counter information about a particular PPP IPXCP session.

xPppIpxcpRxConReq.name: xPppIpxcpRxConReq
